- YOU'RE WONDERING WHY
I PICKED THIS CORNER?

02:56.677 --> 02:58.178
- I'M REALLY NOT.
- WELL, IT'S 'CAUSE--

02:58.178 --> 02:59.513
- YOU CALL ME WHEN
I'M WITH MIKE.

02:59.513 --> 03:01.181
TEXT ME WHEN I'M WITH MIKE.

03:01.181 --> 03:03.309
HOW ABOUT WE JUST CUT OUT
THE MIDDLEMAN, WHICH IS ME,

03:03.309 --> 03:04.727
AND YOU CAN FUCK YOUR BROTHER?

03:04.727 --> 03:07.187
- [chuckles]
I'M BRINGING YOU THERE.

03:07.187 --> 03:10.400
- NO. YOU'RE GOING ON
WITH YOUR LIFE, I'M--

03:10.400 --> 03:12.443
OH, THIS MOTEL?
IT'S CLASSY.

03:12.443 --> 03:16.030
- ROOMS BY THE HOUR.
THAT'S WHY IT'S FUN.

03:16.030 --> 03:17.365
- YOU KNOW HOW LAST TIME

03:17.365 --> 03:18.657
WHEN I TOLD YOU
TO STOP TEXTING ME

03:18.657 --> 03:20.659
AND IT TURNED INTO SEX?

03:20.659 --> 03:22.202
THIS ISN'T THAT.

03:22.202 --> 03:23.621
I DON'T KNOW WHY
IT TOOK ME THIS LONG

03:23.621 --> 03:25.873
TO START HATING MYSELF,
BUT I GOT THERE.

03:25.873 --> 03:28.334
IT'S A SHITTY FEELING.

03:28.334 --> 03:29.793
I'M NOT PUNISHING YOU
OR BLAMING YOU.

03:29.793 --> 03:33.380
I JUST REALLY NEED THIS TO END.

03:33.380 --> 03:36.383
[upbeat rock music]

03:36.383 --> 03:43.807
♪ ♪

03:51.231 --> 03:52.858
- [sighs]

03:52.858 --> 03:56.862
♪ ♪

03:56.862 --> 03:58.864
[door opens]

04:07.081 --> 04:09.458
- PHILLIP GALLAGHER?

04:09.458 --> 04:10.626
- YEAH, WHO'S ASKING?

04:10.626 --> 04:12.086
- FORT DEARBORN MILITARY POLICE.

04:12.086 --> 04:13.504
CAN YOU STEP OUT OF
THE STALL PLEASE?

04:13.504 --> 04:15.547
- YOU KNOW, I'M GONNA BE BUSY
FOR A WHILE,

04:15.547 --> 04:18.425
BUT YOU CAN JOIN ME IF YOU WANT
TO WIPE MY ASS.

04:22.305 --> 04:23.514
WAIT, WHAT THE FUCK, MAN?

04:23.514 --> 04:25.641
HEY, HEY!
- SERGEANT, WAIT!

04:25.641 --> 04:27.059
YOU'RE PHILLIP GALLAGHER?

04:27.059 --> 04:28.769
- JESUS, WHAT THE HELL'S
GOING ON?

04:28.769 --> 04:31.063
OR DO YOU GET OFF ON WATCHING
GUYS TAKING A DUMP?

04:31.063 --> 04:32.439
- IS THAT YOUR
SOCIAL SECURITY NUMBER?

04:32.439 --> 04:35.192
- BLOW ME.
OKAY, YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.

04:35.192 --> 04:36.361
FUCK.

04:36.361 --> 04:39.530
- DO YOU KNOW THIS MAN?

04:39.530 --> 04:42.157
- NO, I'VE NEVER SEEN HIM BEFORE
IN MY LIFE.

04:42.157 --> 04:43.283
- ANY IDEA HOW HE GOT A HOLD OF

04:43.283 --> 04:44.910
YOUR NAME AND SOCIAL SECURITY
NUMBER?

04:44.910 --> 04:47.371
- NO, BUT IT'S PRETTY SCARY,
YOU KNOW?

04:47.371 --> 04:49.665
I'M FEELING PRETTY FUCKING
VIOLATED OVER HERE.

04:52.335 --> 04:53.836
WHAT'S HE, UH,
WHAT'S HE WANTED FOR?

04:53.836 --> 04:56.088
- FOR IMPERSONATING YOU,
APPARENTLY.

04:56.088 --> 04:57.423
ALSO FOR ATTEMPTED THEFT
OF GOVERNMENT PROPERTY

04:57.423 --> 04:58.674
AND BEING AWAY WITHOUT LEAVE.

04:58.674 --> 05:00.551
- WOW, NO SHIT.
WHAT DID HE TRY AND STEAL?

05:00.551 --> 05:02.469
- HELICOPTER.
SURFACE-TO-AIR MISSILE.

05:02.469 --> 05:04.847
ARMY ISSUE BOXER BRIEFS.
- SERGEANT!

05:04.847 --> 05:06.516
- [chuckles]

05:06.516 --> 05:08.767
- MR. GALLAGHER,
WE MAY NEED YOU TO TESTIFY.

05:08.767 --> 05:09.852
WE'LL BE IN TOUCH.

05:09.852 --> 05:11.729
- WELL, AT EASE, GENTLEMEN.

05:15.400 --> 05:17.943
I'VE ALWAYS WANTED TO SAY THAT.

05:19.903 --> 05:22.365
- SO THIS IS IT.

05:22.365 --> 05:23.949
THIS IS WHERE MY DAD LIVES.

05:23.949 --> 05:25.701
- IN ALL ITS GRANDEUR.

05:25.701 --> 05:27.202
- NO ONE'S HOME?

05:27.202 --> 05:29.747
THOUGHT I MIGHT MEET
MY BROTHERS AND SISTERS.

05:29.747 --> 05:31.374
- YEAH, WELL,
THEY'RE PRETTY BUSY.

05:31.374 --> 05:32.542
ANYWAY, WE SHOULD HIT THE ROAD.

05:32.542 --> 05:33.792
TIME TO FIND OUT WHAT THIS

05:33.792 --> 05:35.669
FOOT IS WORTH TO
THE DAMN INSURANCE COMPANY.

05:35.669 --> 05:38.464
- OH.

05:38.464 --> 05:39.423
HERE.

05:39.423 --> 05:41.717
FOR YOUR TOES!
- AH. [laughs]

05:41.717 --> 05:43.635
- COME ON, SIT DOWN.
- [laughs]

05:43.635 --> 05:45.929
- HOPEFULLY, THEY WON'T BREAK
OUR HEARTS AGAIN THIS SEASON.

05:45.929 --> 05:47.639
- [chuckles]

05:47.639 --> 05:51.185
- SO, UM, THERE'S SOMETHING
I HAVE TO SAY.

05:51.185 --> 05:53.353
YOU AND ME, WE HAVE...

05:53.353 --> 05:55.063
A CONNECTION.

05:55.063 --> 05:57.483
I MEAN, LAST WEEK I WAS TRYING
TO GET YOU INTO THE SACK.

05:57.483 --> 06:00.194
- IT'S UNDERSTANDABLE
UNDER THE CIRCUMSTANCES.

06:00.194 --> 06:01.862
- I THOUGHT,
"THE SEX IS GONNA BE AMAZING,"

06:01.862 --> 06:05.115
AND THEN I FOUND OUT
YOU WERE MY DAD,

06:05.115 --> 06:09.703
SO THAT WAS, LIKE...
AN ADJUSTMENT.

06:09.703 --> 06:12.498
- SURE.

06:13.707 --> 06:15.793
- MY WHOLE LIFE,

06:15.793 --> 06:17.795
I'VE BEEN LOOKING FOR A DADDY.

06:19.922 --> 06:23.550
THE OLD MEN WHO'D GET LUCKY
WITH ME AT LAST CALL,

06:23.550 --> 06:26.929
THE BASS PLAYER WHO GOT HERPES
IN MANILA,

06:26.929 --> 06:31.266
AND NOW, AT LAST, I HAVE YOU.

06:31.266 --> 06:33.185
ONLY--

06:33.185 --> 06:34.604
- WHAT?

06:34.604 --> 06:35.771
- YOU DIDN'T COME FIND ME

06:35.771 --> 06:38.023
BECAUSE YOU NEED
ANOTHER DAUGHTER.

06:38.023 --> 06:41.443
YOU JUST NEED A LIVER, RIGHT?
AND I'M GONNA HELP YOU FIND ONE,

06:41.443 --> 06:43.320
BUT IF THAT'S ALL THIS IS...

06:43.320 --> 06:44.863
- NO, NO.
- THEN I--

06:44.863 --> 06:47.282
- NO.

06:47.282 --> 06:51.537
I MEAN, YES, INITIALLY I SORT OF
LOOKED AT YOU AS AN ORGAN FARM,

06:51.537 --> 06:54.414
BUT WHEN YOU FIGURED OUT
WE WERE FAMILY,

06:54.414 --> 06:57.292
YOU DIDN'T TREAT ME LIKE
THE REST OF MY KIDS--

06:57.292 --> 06:59.462
RATS LEAVING A SINKING SHIP.

06:59.462 --> 07:01.046
AND, HELL,
I WOULDN'T HAVE BLAMED YOU.

07:01.046 --> 07:02.923
BUT YOU STUCK AROUND.

07:02.923 --> 07:05.468
YOU GAVE ME HOPE.

07:07.010 --> 07:09.429
- OH.
[sniffles]

07:09.429 --> 07:11.139
I'M SORRY.

07:11.139 --> 07:14.393
I HATE TO CRY.
OH.

07:14.393 --> 07:16.436
- I'D BE CRYING TOO
IF I WASN'T SO HIGH.

07:16.436 --> 07:20.440
- [laughs]

07:23.277 --> 07:26.029
COME ON, DADDY.

07:26.029 --> 07:27.406
LET'S GO GET YOU
SOME MONEY, HUH?

07:27.406 --> 07:28.491
- MM.

07:28.491 --> 07:31.494
[soft rock music]

07:31.494 --> 07:38.876
♪ ♪

07:41.712 --> 07:43.463
- HEY, YOU WANNA GUESS.

07:43.463 --> 07:44.715
- GUESS WHAT?

07:44.715 --> 07:46.508
- WHAT WE'RE DOING
FOR YOUR BIRTHDAY.

07:46.508 --> 07:48.635
- HMM.
GOING DANCING?

07:48.635 --> 07:51.681
- MM-MM.
- I MEAN, SKYDIVING?

07:51.681 --> 07:54.474
- MM.
- [gasps] SEX CLUB?

07:54.474 --> 07:56.935
[gasps] I KNEW IT.
SEX CLUB.

07:56.935 --> 07:59.771
I'LL WEAR MY CROTCHLESS TEDDY.
- UH, COCKTAIL ATTIRE.

07:59.771 --> 08:02.107
WEAR SOMETHING WARM IN CASE
WE WANT TO HANG OUTSIDE.

08:02.107 --> 08:05.110
- AH, I'VE NEVER BEEN TO
AN OUTDOOR SEX CLUB.

08:05.110 --> 08:06.612
- [laughs]
OH, YEAH, YOU KNOW WHAT?

08:06.612 --> 08:08.906
SPEAKING OF ROMANTIC,
INTIMATE GETAWAYS--MY MOM.

08:08.906 --> 08:10.324
- EW.

08:10.324 --> 08:11.700
- SHE WANTED US
TO COME GRILL TONIGHT.

08:11.700 --> 08:13.703
- SHE DID?
- MM-HMM.

08:13.703 --> 08:15.621
- THAT'S SO NICE.
- YEAH.

08:15.621 --> 08:17.540
SO IT'S JUST US.
AND ROBBIE.

08:17.540 --> 08:18.541
AND MY PARENTS.
IS THAT OKAY?

08:18.541 --> 08:20.543
- PERFECT.
SURE.

08:23.962 --> 08:26.548
[jackhammer pounding]
- I OWN THE ALIBI ROOM!

08:26.548 --> 08:29.635
IT'S A BAR,
WHICH YOU MAY NOT KNOW,

08:29.635 --> 08:32.930
BECAUSE YOUR FUCKING SCAFFOLDING
IS COVERING THE SIGN!

08:32.930 --> 08:35.558
[jackhammer pounding]
- UH-HUH.

08:35.558 --> 08:38.603
- YOUR GUY SAID THAT--
[jackhammer pounding]

08:38.603 --> 08:39.519
YOUR--YOUR--
[jackhammer pounding]

08:39.519 --> 08:41.146
EXCUSE ME!

08:41.146 --> 08:43.315
CAN YOU PLEASE STOP
JACKHAMMERING

08:43.315 --> 08:45.400
FOR ONE MINUTE?
THANK YOU!

08:45.400 --> 08:47.903
YOUR GUYS SAID THE SCAFFOLDING
IS TO CHECK THE BUILDING

08:47.903 --> 08:49.905
FOR LOOSE BRICKS OR SOMETHING.
- CORRECT.

08:49.905 --> 08:53.743
- YEAH, THEN WHY ARE YOU
DIGGING UP THE SIDEWALK?

08:53.743 --> 08:54.993
- NEW SEWER LINE.

08:54.993 --> 08:57.537
- I DEPEND ON WALK-IN BUSINESS,
ALL RIGHT?

08:57.537 --> 08:58.914
CUSTOMERS SEE THE SIGN,
THEY GO,

08:58.914 --> 09:00.374
"HEY, THAT'S A NICE BAR.

09:00.374 --> 09:01.500
I WANT A DRINK THERE."

09:01.500 --> 09:02.834
HERE'S THE IMPORTANT PART.

09:02.834 --> 09:06.129
THEY NEED THE SIDEWALK
TO WALK INTO MY BAR!

09:06.129 --> 09:07.673
HOW LONG?

09:07.673 --> 09:08.674
[jackhammer pounding]
- WHAT?

09:08.674 --> 09:10.718
- HOW LONG IS IT GONNA BE
TORN UP?

09:10.718 --> 09:11.551
A DAY OR TWO?

09:11.551 --> 09:13.387
- MORE LIKE SIX OR SEVEN.

09:13.387 --> 09:14.680
- SEVEN DAYS?

09:14.680 --> 09:19.643
- WEEKS.
[jackhammer pounding]

09:19.643 --> 09:21.186
- FUCK!

09:21.186 --> 09:27.192
[cartoons in background]

09:35.618 --> 09:35.660
- HEY.

09:36.619 --> 09:37.662
- NO WAY.
- LIP!

09:37.662 --> 09:38.954
YOU'RE HOME!
- HEY.

09:38.954 --> 09:40.665
THOUGHT IT WAS TIME
I STOPPED BY, CHECK IN.

09:40.665 --> 09:43.166
- HOW ARE THE COEDS?
- OH, IT VARIES BY COED.

09:43.166 --> 09:45.752
WHAT'S THIS?
- CREEPY ART SHE'S MAKING

09:45.752 --> 09:47.587
'CAUSE HER BOYFRIEND DUMPED HER.
- A BOYFRIEND?

09:47.587 --> 09:49.423
- I'M EXPRESSING MYSELF
CREATIVELY.

09:49.423 --> 09:51.383
YOU'RE COUNTING UNDERARM HAIR
WITH A MIRROR.

09:51.383 --> 09:52.467
- CHECK IT OUT, FOUR NEW ONES.

09:52.467 --> 09:55.178
- GET OFF OF ME!

09:55.178 --> 09:57.055
- PHILLIP!

09:57.055 --> 09:58.766
HOW NICE!

09:58.766 --> 10:00.017
NO ONE TOLD ME YOU'D BE HOME!

10:00.017 --> 10:01.769
- SHEILA, WHA--
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

10:01.769 --> 10:02.812
- GOOD QUESTION.

10:02.812 --> 10:05.272
- WELL, FIONA'S AT WORK,

10:05.272 --> 10:06.815
AND THEN SHE HAS A BARBECUE
AT MIKE'S HOUSE,

10:06.815 --> 10:08.817
AND I SAID I'D BE HAPPY
TO WATCH THE KIDS.

10:08.817 --> 10:11.236
- NICE, AND YOU AND LIAM HERE
HAVING A CANDLE-LIT DINNER?

10:11.236 --> 10:12.904
- WELL...
[Native American music]

10:12.904 --> 10:15.282
FIONA SAID IT WAS OKAY
IF I HAD MY DATE OVER.

10:15.282 --> 10:16.450
IT'S ACTUALLY OUR FOURTH DATE.

10:16.450 --> 10:17.826
HE'S SUCH AN INTERESTING MAN.

10:17.826 --> 10:19.286
[chanting grows louder]
- WHAT'S THE MUSIC?

10:19.286 --> 10:21.706
- "TRIBAL TWILIGHT:
RECORDED SONGS

10:21.706 --> 10:24.541
OF THE MENOMINEE INDIAN TRIBE."
[timer dings]

10:24.541 --> 10:26.084
THAT WOULD BE MY SUCCOTASH.
HOLD ON.

10:26.084 --> 10:29.212
[chanting continues]
- OKAY.

10:29.212 --> 10:30.297
[music stops]

10:32.758 --> 10:34.134
THERE YOU GO.

10:34.134 --> 10:36.470
HEY, UM, YOU GUYS HEARD ANYTHING
FROM IAN?

10:36.470 --> 10:38.806
- NOT FOR WEEKS.
AND FIONA DOESN'T EVEN CARE.

10:38.806 --> 10:42.559
- WHAT ABOUT THE U.S. ARMY.
YOU HEAR ANYTHING FROM THEM?

10:42.559 --> 10:43.977
- WE'RE LOOKING
FOR PHILLIP GALLAGHER.

10:43.977 --> 10:47.064
- HE'S AT COLLEGE.

10:47.064 --> 10:48.648
NO.
- WHY THE ARMY?

10:48.648 --> 10:51.151
- 'CAUSE IAN JOINED UP.
- COOL.

10:51.151 --> 10:52.736
- IS HE OLD ENOUGH?

10:52.736 --> 10:55.405
- NO, HE USED MY NAME
AND SOCIAL WHEN HE SIGNED UP,

10:55.405 --> 10:57.783
AND THEN HE TRIED TO STEAL
A HELICOPTER

10:57.783 --> 10:59.493
AND A BUNCH OF OTHER SHIT.
WENT AWOL.

10:59.493 --> 11:00.786
- HELICOPTER?
AWESOME.

11:00.786 --> 11:01.912
- DOES FIONA KNOW?
- NO, NOT YET.

11:01.912 --> 11:03.413
YOU KNOW WHEN
SHE'S GONNA BE BACK?

11:03.413 --> 11:05.207
- SHE DOESN'T ALWAYS COME HOME.

11:05.207 --> 11:08.251
LOTS OF SHEILA BABYSITTING.
- YOU COULD CALL HER.

11:08.251 --> 11:09.377
- NO, IT'S NOT THE KIND
OF NEWS YOU WANT

11:09.377 --> 11:10.880
TO DELIVER ON THE PHONE.

11:10.880 --> 11:12.130
HEY, IS THAT YOUR BOYFRIEND

11:12.130 --> 11:14.174
WITH THE TOOTHPICKS IN HIS HEAD?

11:14.174 --> 11:16.301
- IT'S SORT OF ABSTRACT.
I'M CALLING IT "TRUE LOVE."

11:16.301 --> 11:17.719
- SUPER CREEPY.

11:17.719 --> 11:19.888
- COLLECTORS WILL PAY MILLIONS
FOR IT ONE DAY.

11:19.888 --> 11:23.975
AN EARLY WORK FROM DEBBIE
GALLAGHER'S COLLAGE PHASE.

11:23.975 --> 11:26.520
I'LL SEE YOU GUYS LATER, OKAY?
- WHERE YOU GOING?

11:26.520 --> 11:28.438
- I'M GONNA GO ASK AROUND
ABOUT IAN.

11:28.438 --> 11:29.856
SEE IF ANYONE'S HEARD FROM HIM.

11:29.856 --> 11:30.941
- OKAY.
- BYE.

11:30.941 --> 11:32.192
[door closes]

11:32.192 --> 11:33.985
- LIKE YOU KNOW ANYTHING
ABOUT ART.

11:39.699 --> 11:41.535
- ALL RIGHT, TURN TO THE LEFT.

11:41.535 --> 11:43.537
AND RAISE THE LEG.

11:45.122 --> 11:47.958
YEAH, NOW MAKE A SAD FACE.

11:47.958 --> 11:49.334
- WHAT, DO I LOOK HAPPY?

11:49.334 --> 11:50.753
[camera shutter clicks]

11:50.753 --> 11:52.254
- OH, MAN.

11:52.254 --> 11:54.381
TOTALLY THOUGHT YOU WERE GONNA
WUSS OUT ON ME ON THIS,

11:54.381 --> 11:56.007
COME BACK WITH A HAIRLINE
FRACTURE, BUT THIS?

11:56.007 --> 11:57.843
THIS IS A MASTERPIECE.

11:57.843 --> 12:00.178
I MEAN, THIS IS LIKE A AERIAL
PHOTO OF GROUND ZERO.

12:00.178 --> 12:01.596
YOU SHOULD BE VERY PROUD.

12:01.596 --> 12:03.181
- JUST TELL ME
WE CAN GET 100 GRAND.

12:03.181 --> 12:05.392
- OH, I'D SAY 100 "G"s, EASY.

12:05.392 --> 12:06.726
- THAT'S WONDERFUL.

12:06.726 --> 12:08.896
- I AM JUST GOING TO GET
MY HANDS ON THE FORMS.

12:08.896 --> 12:10.689
SHE SIGNS AS A WITNESS, RIGHT?

12:10.689 --> 12:14.901
WE FILE THE CLAIM, AND THEN
YOU GET A CHECK IN 16 MONTHS.

12:14.901 --> 12:17.779
- WHAT--16 MONTHS?
NO, THAT'S TOO LONG.

12:17.779 --> 12:19.614
MY LIVER IS FAILING NOW.

12:19.614 --> 12:21.283
- WELL, I CAN PUSH FOR
A QUICK SETTLEMENT.

12:21.283 --> 12:23.910
- HOW QUICK.
- A YEAR?

12:23.910 --> 12:27.122
HEY, FRANK, THEY'RE NOT GONNA
JUST HAND YOU THE CASH, OKAY?

12:27.122 --> 12:29.834
SUCK IT UP AND SURVIVE.

12:33.003 --> 12:36.339
- STAY WITH ME TONIGHT.
I'LL TAKE CARE OF YOU.

12:36.339 --> 12:38.675
- I'M GONNA NEED MORE MEDS.

12:38.675 --> 12:41.678
[upbeat rock music]

12:41.678 --> 12:49.102
♪ ♪

12:50.270 --> 12:52.314
- HEY.

12:52.314 --> 12:53.857
- MANDY AIN'T HERE.

12:53.857 --> 12:57.360
- THAT'S GOOD, 'CAUSE I CAME
TO TALK TO YOU.

12:57.360 --> 12:58.862
- THE FUCK YOU WANT?

12:58.862 --> 13:01.740
- YOU HEARD ANYTHING FROM IAN?

13:01.740 --> 13:03.283
- NO.

13:04.910 --> 13:05.785
- IT'S IMPORTANT.

13:05.785 --> 13:07.120
- SO YOU THINK I GIVE A SHIT

13:07.120 --> 13:10.833
'CAUSE I WORKED WITH THE GUY?

13:10.833 --> 13:14.127
- YOU'RE GONNA MAKE ME
SPELL IT OUT?

13:14.127 --> 13:16.338
- WHAT THE FUCK YOU GETTING AT?

13:16.338 --> 13:18.506
- NOTHING, I'M JUST WORRIED
ABOUT HIM.

13:18.506 --> 13:19.633
THAT'S ALL.

13:19.633 --> 13:22.302
- WELL, I HAVEN'T SEEN HIM.

13:22.302 --> 13:24.304
- HOW HARD WAS THAT?

13:24.304 --> 13:27.891
- HE IN TROUBLE?
- [sniffs]

13:27.891 --> 13:30.310
- WHAT KIND OF TROUBLE?

13:30.310 --> 13:33.688
- I'LL TELL YOU WHEN I FIND OUT.

13:39.069 --> 13:41.863
- ROBBIE, TELL THEM WHAT YOU
WERE SAYING ABOUT THE TURKEY.

13:41.863 --> 13:43.281
- YEAH?
- TURKEY?

13:43.281 --> 13:45.200
- WHEN I WAS AT TED'S IN OREGON,

13:45.200 --> 13:47.535
HE WANTED ME TO TRY
HIS FAMOUS DEEP-FRIED TURKEY.

13:47.535 --> 13:50.330
[chuckling]
SO WE PUT THIS HOT OIL PRESSURE

13:50.330 --> 13:51.999
COOKER THING IN THE YARD...
- RIGHT.

13:51.999 --> 13:54.834
- AND PUT THE TURKEY IN,
AND IT EXPLODED.

13:54.834 --> 13:56.253
SET THE ENTIRE SIDE OF
HIS HOUSE ON FIRE.

13:56.253 --> 13:58.922
- NO WAY.
- FIRE TRUCKS, ALL THAT.

13:58.922 --> 14:00.340
THEY PUT THE FIRE OUT,

14:00.340 --> 14:02.175
AND THE HOUSE
WAS MORE OR LESS OKAY.

14:02.175 --> 14:03.468
BUT THEN WE SAW THE TURKEY
BY THE SWIMMING POOL.

14:03.468 --> 14:04.886
- THIS IS REALLY GOOD.

14:04.886 --> 14:06.931
- OH, YOU'VE HEARD THIS?
- PULL A DRUMSTICK OFF

14:06.931 --> 14:08.848
AND TRY IT...
[chuckles]

14:08.848 --> 14:10.934
AND IT WAS REALLY, REALLY GOOD!
[laughter]

14:10.934 --> 14:11.977
- CAN YOU BELIEVE IT?
[laughs]

14:11.977 --> 14:14.104
- WOW.
- THAT'S FUNNY.

14:14.104 --> 14:16.941
- MM.
- YEAH.

14:16.941 --> 14:19.859
DID DAD TELL YOU HOW
I WANT TO MOVE TO PORTLAND?

14:19.859 --> 14:21.820
- NO.
- OH, THAT'S INTERESTING.

14:21.820 --> 14:24.281
'CAUSE HE SAID HE SPOKE TO YOU
AND YOU WERE THE ONE

14:24.281 --> 14:28.285
WHO TALKED HIM OUT OF WRITING
THE CHECK TO COVER MY MOVE.

14:28.285 --> 14:31.162
- NO, HE DIDN'T MENTION THAT
YOU WERE MOVING TO OREGON.

14:31.162 --> 14:33.039
- HMM.
- CAN WE NOT DO THIS

14:33.039 --> 14:35.458
WITH A GUEST HERE?
- WHAT, FIONA?

14:35.458 --> 14:37.086
SHE'S PRACTICALLY FAMILY,
MOM.

14:37.086 --> 14:37.961
- LOOK, ROBBIE,
I HAVEN'T TOLD DAD ANYTHING

14:37.961 --> 14:39.754
THAT I HAVEN'T SAID TO YOU,

14:39.754 --> 14:41.131
ALL RIGHT, AND I THINK IT'S
A SMART IDEA FOR--

14:41.131 --> 14:43.008
- I DON'T TELL YOU WHAT TO DO.

14:43.008 --> 14:44.759
AND SO IF YOU WANT TO SELL CUPS
FOR THE REST OF YOUR LIFE

14:44.759 --> 14:46.971
WITH DAD, GO FOR IT, ALL RIGHT?
SIT BEHIND A FAKE WOOD DESK

14:46.971 --> 14:48.346
ALL DAY AND MAKE PAYMENTS
ON YOUR DUPLEX

14:48.346 --> 14:50.140
AND YOUR COOL DODGE CHALLENGER.

14:50.140 --> 14:53.393
- WHAT, ARE YOU CHASING
YOUR DREAMS, IS THAT IT?

14:53.393 --> 14:55.395
HOW'S THAT WORKING OUT, ROBBIE?

14:59.065 --> 15:00.608
- FIONA...
[door slams]

15:00.608 --> 15:02.569
CAN YOU GIVE ME A HAND WITH
THE SKEWERS?

15:02.569 --> 15:05.990
- I'D LOVE TO.
- THANKS.

15:05.990 --> 15:08.366
[sighs]
RIGHT HERE.

15:08.366 --> 15:09.951
- I DON'T HAVE ANYTHING
AGAINST--

15:09.951 --> 15:13.038
- THAT LAKEBOAT LOOKS GORGEOUS
AT NIGHT, ALL LIT UP.

15:13.038 --> 15:14.873
- WHAT?
WHAT LAKEBOAT?

15:14.873 --> 15:16.624
- MIKE SAID FOR YOUR BIRTHDAY--
- UH, BILL!

15:16.624 --> 15:18.209
IT WAS A SURPRISE.

15:18.209 --> 15:19.461
- I THOUGHT IT WAS--
- OH, HE MADE IT

15:19.461 --> 15:21.088
PERFECTLY CLEAR.

15:21.088 --> 15:22.672
- OH, SHIT, I'M SORRY.

15:22.672 --> 15:24.174
- I'LL PRETEND I'M SURPRISED.
- [chuckles]

15:24.174 --> 15:25.759
- AND NOW THAT YOU MENTION IT,
IT DOES SOUND FUN.

15:25.759 --> 15:27.094
- IT'S WONDERFUL.

15:27.094 --> 15:28.845
I TOOK NANCY THERE
A FEW YEARS AGO.

15:28.845 --> 15:29.971
- AW, IT WAS SO ROMANTIC.

15:29.971 --> 15:32.057
- GOT A TABLE BY THE WINDOW.

15:32.057 --> 15:33.183
THERE'S SEATING ON THE OUTSIDE,

15:33.183 --> 15:34.434
BUT IT GETS PRETTY COLD
OUT THERE.

15:34.434 --> 15:36.061
- JUST BRING A WARM COAT.

15:36.061 --> 15:39.689
- THERE'S A LIT DANCE FLOOR
AND, I GUESS, A D.J.

15:39.689 --> 15:41.316
OR A LIVE BAND, DEPENDING.

15:41.316 --> 15:42.525
WE JUST SAT AT OUR TABLE,
GOT--

15:42.525 --> 15:43.902
[both gasp]
- GOD DAMN IT!

15:43.902 --> 15:46.237
- WHAT?
- STOP IT, YOU TWO--

15:46.237 --> 15:48.115
STOP! STOP IT, STOP!

15:48.115 --> 15:49.657
- OH, MY GOD.
- FUCK!

15:49.657 --> 15:50.700
- STOP IT!

15:50.700 --> 15:52.994
- WHAT HAPPENED?
- STOP IT.

15:54.704 --> 15:57.540
- WHAT DID YOU SAY?

15:57.540 --> 16:00.251
[door opens, closes]

16:09.052 --> 16:11.054
EVERYTHING OKAY?

16:15.183 --> 16:16.393
I'LL WAIT INSIDE.

16:16.393 --> 16:18.728
- NO, YOU SHOULD GO.

16:22.023 --> 16:23.233
- MIKE, I DON'T KNOW WHAT
HE SA--

16:23.233 --> 16:25.235
- PLEASE, JUST GO.

16:30.824 --> 16:32.951
- ACTUALLY,
MY DECEASED EX-HUSBAND

16:32.951 --> 16:34.452
HAD VERY STRONG
CHRISTIAN BELIEFS,

16:34.452 --> 16:35.995
AND I WOULD GO TO CHURCH
WITH HIM,

16:35.995 --> 16:39.207
BUT I'VE GOT TO ADMIT,
IT'S BEEN A WHILE.

16:39.207 --> 16:41.085
- I'M NOT A CHRISTIAN.
- WHAT?

16:41.085 --> 16:43.795
BUT THE--THE WEBSITE
WAS CHRISTIAN-MINGLE.COM.

16:43.795 --> 16:45.296
- GOOD WAY TO MEET
NICE WHITE WOMEN.

16:45.296 --> 16:47.757
- OH, WELL, I'LL TAKE THAT
AS A COMPLIMENT.

16:47.757 --> 16:49.592
- MY EYES ENJOY YOU.
- OH!

16:49.592 --> 16:51.095
- DON'T LET ME INTERRUPT.

16:51.095 --> 16:54.556
I STASHED SOME THC EDIBLES
IN THE FREEZER.

16:54.556 --> 16:55.723
I GOTTA--

16:59.103 --> 17:01.688
WHAT WAS YOUR NAME AGAIN?
CLIMBING WEED?

17:01.688 --> 17:03.857
- RUNNING TREE.
- OH.

17:03.857 --> 17:05.900
YOU'RE INDIAN?
THE FEATHER, NOT THE DOT?

17:05.900 --> 17:08.069
- HE'S A MENOMINEE INDIAN,
FRANK.

17:08.069 --> 17:10.239
WE BOTH ARE, ACTUALLY.

17:10.239 --> 17:14.076
MY GREAT-GRANDMOTHER WAS RAPED
BY A MENOMINEE WARRIOR,

17:14.076 --> 17:15.910
AND I'M LEARNING ALL ABOUT
THE CULTURE.

17:15.910 --> 17:18.955
- ISN'T THIS A GREAT COUNTRY?
- YEAH.

17:18.955 --> 17:23.585
- JUST ONE, BIG, RAPEY
MELTING POT.

17:23.585 --> 17:25.920
- FRANK, WE'RE JUST--
WE'RE HAVING DINNER.

17:25.920 --> 17:27.380
- NO, I'M FINE.

17:29.883 --> 17:31.801
CAN I ASK YOU
A DELICATE QUESTION?

17:31.801 --> 17:33.303
- THANKS.

17:33.303 --> 17:34.804
- ON THE INDIAN RESERVATION,

17:34.804 --> 17:36.556
YOU PEOPLE DRINK YOURSELVES
UNCONSCIOUS,

17:36.556 --> 17:39.392
BUT I NEVER HEAR OF AN INDIAN
GETTING A LIVER TRANSPLANT.

17:39.392 --> 17:42.479
WHY IS THAT?
- GOVERNMENT WON'T PAY FOR IT.

17:42.479 --> 17:44.147
- BASTARDS.

17:44.147 --> 17:46.149
- SO WE USE A SWEAT LODGE.
- YEAH?

17:46.149 --> 17:47.525
- IT'S A CEREMONY.

17:47.525 --> 17:49.110
IT CLEANS YOUR LIVER,
YOUR SPLEEN.

17:49.110 --> 17:52.238
OPENS YOUR SOUL
TO THE GREAT SPIRIT.

17:52.238 --> 17:53.740
AND IT'S A REAL HIGH.

17:53.740 --> 17:57.035
RELEASES THE TOXINS
IN YOUR FAT CELLS.

17:57.035 --> 18:00.830
IT'S LIKE SNORTING OXY, MAN.
IT'S BEAUTIFUL.

18:00.830 --> 18:04.959
- DO--DO YOU THINK IT WOULD WORK
FOR MY LIVER?

18:04.959 --> 18:08.046
THIS BABY'S ON ITS LAST LEGS.
- NO QUESTION.

18:08.046 --> 18:10.465
BUT I LIVE IN A CONDO.
NO PLACE TO BUILD A LODGE.

18:10.465 --> 18:13.510
- WELL, YOU COULD USE MY YARD.

18:13.510 --> 18:14.969
- THAT WOULD BE ALL RIGHT
WITH YOU?

18:14.969 --> 18:17.555
- OH, I THINK IT WOULD BE
JUST WONDERFUL.

18:17.555 --> 18:20.225
- HMM.
IT'S BEEN A WHILE.

18:20.225 --> 18:22.227
BUT, HELL YES.
LET'S DO IT.

18:22.227 --> 18:25.355
- FUCK WESTERN MEDICINE.
- TO SWEATIN' IT OUT.

18:25.355 --> 18:27.482
- TO SWEATING IT OUT.

18:27.482 --> 18:28.983
- TO SWEATIN' IT OUT!

18:30.276 --> 18:32.153
- WHAT IS THAT?

18:32.153 --> 18:33.571
- I'M GONNA PUT
THIS SIGN OUTSIDE

18:33.571 --> 18:36.115
SO PEOPLE KNOW TO COME IN
THE BACK.

18:37.951 --> 18:40.162
- YOU REALIZE THAT'S NOT HOW
YOU SPELL "COME," RIGHT?

18:41.746 --> 18:45.416
- SHIT.
- BABY, HE SAW YOU.

18:45.416 --> 18:47.169
- ALAN.

18:47.169 --> 18:48.586
HOW ARE YOU, MY FRIEND?
WHAT CAN I GET YOU?

18:48.586 --> 18:50.213
- WELL, LET'S SEE.
I'LL START WITH TWO

18:50.213 --> 18:54.176
LEGALLY-MANDATED MONTHLY
PAYMENTS OF $500 EACH.

18:54.176 --> 18:55.843
- AND I'D LOVE TO GIVE THEM
TO YOU,

18:55.843 --> 18:57.762
BUT THIS BAR IS
A FINANCIAL BLACK HOLE.

18:57.762 --> 18:59.472
AND NOW THE CITY HAS BLOCKED
OUR FRONT DOOR,

18:59.472 --> 19:01.558
SO PEOPLE THINK WE ARE CLOSED.

19:01.558 --> 19:03.935
- THE MINUTE WE TURN IT AROUND
YOU'LL GET PAID, I PROMISE.

19:03.935 --> 19:06.563
- WELL, YOU'RE KEEPING UP WITH
MY FATHER'S LEGACY.

19:06.563 --> 19:08.147
- WE'RE TRYING.
- VIOLATING MY TRUST

19:08.147 --> 19:09.274
AND SCREWING ME OVER!

19:09.274 --> 19:11.943
EVEN DEAD, HE FUCKS ME!

19:11.943 --> 19:15.154
$1,000, TOMORROW.
UNDERSTAND?

19:17.156 --> 19:18.992
- WAS HE THREATENING US?

19:18.992 --> 19:21.578
- YEAH, HE'S GONNA BEAT US
TO DEATH WITH HIS LIMP WRIST.

19:21.578 --> 19:23.329
- THOUGH HE DID INHERIT
HIS FATHER'S GUN COLLECTION.

19:23.329 --> 19:24.914
- [sighs]
TRUE.

19:24.914 --> 19:26.374
- AND HIS DADDY
WAS A LOAN SHARK.

19:26.374 --> 19:28.293
HE MIGHT HAVE LEARNED
A FEW TRICKS OF THE TRADE.

19:28.293 --> 19:30.336
- SO FAR, THIS DAY
HAS SUCKED ASS.

19:32.171 --> 19:33.798
- WHAT KIND OF CLUES
ARE WE LOOKING FOR?

19:33.798 --> 19:36.092
- UH, A FRIEND OF IAN
WE DON'T KNOW ABOUT,

19:36.092 --> 19:38.469
AN ADDRESS.
ANYTHING, REALLY.

19:38.469 --> 19:40.179
- HE REALLY STOLE A HELICOPTER?

19:40.179 --> 19:42.265
DOESN'T SOUND LIKE IAN.
- NO.

19:44.642 --> 19:47.228
- YOU'RE WORRIED?

19:47.228 --> 19:49.063
- YEAH.
YEAH, YOU KNOW,

19:49.063 --> 19:51.816
IT WOULD BE NICE TO FIND HIM
BEFORE THE ARMY DOES.

19:51.816 --> 19:53.985
- I CAN HELP LOOK FOR HIM
AFTER SCHOOL TOMORROW.

19:53.985 --> 19:56.195
- IT WOULD BE GREAT IF
YOU COULD TALK TO MANDY.

19:56.195 --> 19:59.490
- YOU DON'T WANT TO?
- [sighs]

19:59.490 --> 20:01.409
- SHE'S MAD AT YOU, ISN'T SHE?

20:01.409 --> 20:05.913
- YEAH, WE RECONNECTED,
AND THINGS GOT COMPLICATED.

20:05.913 --> 20:08.833
- DID YOU HAVE SEX?
- WHAT?

20:08.833 --> 20:10.168
- YOU DON'T HAVE TO TELL ME.

20:10.168 --> 20:13.463
- YEAH, BUT...

20:13.463 --> 20:16.257
YOU KNOW, IT WAS NO BIG DEAL.

20:16.257 --> 20:21.220
- IF IT WASN'T SEX,
THEN WHAT WAS THE PROBLEM?

20:21.220 --> 20:23.222
- EVERYTHING ELSE.

20:31.856 --> 20:33.149
- OH!

20:33.149 --> 20:34.442
- TELL ME WHAT YOU TOLD MIKE!

20:34.442 --> 20:35.902
- THE TRUTH!
HE NEEDED TO KNOW.

20:35.902 --> 20:37.528
OH!

20:37.528 --> 20:41.366
- OH, THAT WAS FOR HIS SAKE?
HOW GENEROUS.

20:41.366 --> 20:42.367
- I DID YOU A FAVOR, OKAY?

20:42.367 --> 20:44.243
- FUCK YOU.

20:44.243 --> 20:46.371
- YOU DON'T WANT TO BE WITH HIM.

20:46.371 --> 20:48.332
- YOU DON'T KNOW SHIT ABOUT ME.

20:48.332 --> 20:50.708
[spits]

21:03.347 --> 21:05.432
- OH!
- SHIT!

21:05.432 --> 21:07.351
- YOU'VE GOT TO BE KIDDING ME.

21:07.351 --> 21:09.477
[glass breaks]

21:09.477 --> 21:11.479
- AH!
- UH--'SCUSE--

21:13.106 --> 21:15.442
HEY, YOU MIND NOT SWINGING
THAT SHIT AROUND?

21:15.442 --> 21:16.693
YOU'RE GONNA FUCKIN'
HURT SOMEONE.

21:16.693 --> 21:18.445
- THIS IS YOUR FAULT!
- MINE?

21:18.445 --> 21:19.696
- I'M PRACTICALLY TRIPPING
OVER THESE BITCHES.

21:19.696 --> 21:21.489
I WANT THEM GONE, NOW!

21:21.489 --> 21:24.617
I WAS GONE TEN FUCKING MINUTES!

21:24.617 --> 21:27.036
[door slams]

21:28.287 --> 21:31.374
[phone rings]

21:31.374 --> 21:32.750
- YO, IT'S MICKEY.
IN OR OUT?

21:32.750 --> 21:34.585
- I TOLD YOU, I'M IN.

21:34.585 --> 21:37.296
I'M JUST NOT LOOKING FORWARD
TO DISCUSSING IT WITH MY WIFE.

21:37.296 --> 21:39.799
I'LL CALL YOU BACK.
[phone beeps]

21:39.799 --> 21:41.217
BABY?

21:41.217 --> 21:42.927
- YEAH?
- YOU KNOW HOW WE WERE TALKING

21:42.927 --> 21:45.096
ABOUT USING STAN'S APARTMENT
TO GENERATE SOME INCOME?

21:45.096 --> 21:46.389
- RENT IT OUT.

21:46.389 --> 21:48.599
- OR, WE COULD OPEN UP
ANOTHER BUSINESS.

21:48.599 --> 21:50.393
- SINCE THIS ONE
IS GOING SO WELL.

21:50.393 --> 21:52.603
YOU KNOW HOW EXPENSIVE IT IS
TO GET A BUSINESS LICENSE?

21:52.603 --> 21:54.439
- UNLESS WE DON'T NEED ONE.

21:54.439 --> 21:56.065
SVETLANA AND HER GIRLS
ARE OUT OF WORK--

21:56.065 --> 21:57.817
- WAIT. WAIT A MINUTE.
[laughs]

21:57.817 --> 21:59.402
DO YOU WANT TO OPEN
A WHOREHOUSE?

21:59.402 --> 22:01.779
- NO, OF COURSE NOT!

22:01.779 --> 22:03.448
JUST A RUB AND TUG.

22:03.448 --> 22:04.407
IT'S A MASSAGE WITH
A HAPPY ENDING.

22:04.407 --> 22:05.950
- I KNOW WHAT A RUB AND TUG IS.

22:05.950 --> 22:07.994
- THOSE GIRLS
ARE TRAINED PROFESSIONALS.

22:07.994 --> 22:09.829
AND COMPARED TO THIS PLACE,
IT'S PURE PROFIT.

22:09.829 --> 22:13.332
BABY, LOOK, WE ARE VICTIMS OF
A SOCIETY THAT SQUEEZES

22:13.332 --> 22:15.710
THE LOWER MIDDLE CLASS,
SCREWS UP OUR BUSINESSES

22:15.710 --> 22:18.671
BECAUSE OF JACKHAMMERS
AND TAXES AND REGULATIONS

22:18.671 --> 22:20.256
AND UNNECESSARY PAPERWORK,

22:20.256 --> 22:22.216
BASICALLY FORCES US
TO DO ILLEGAL SHIT.

22:22.216 --> 22:24.343
NOW I'M HAVING FOUR KIDS!

22:24.343 --> 22:26.637
AND IF THAT MEANS I'VE GOT
TO TURN OUT SOME RUSSIAN WHORES

22:26.637 --> 22:29.640
TO FEED MY FAMILY AND PURSUE
THE AMERICAN DREAM,

22:29.640 --> 22:31.392
THAT'S HOW IT'S GOTTA BE!

22:31.392 --> 22:35.688
[applause]

22:35.688 --> 22:38.274
- I WAS GONNA SAY
I THINK IT'S A GREAT IDEA.

22:38.274 --> 22:40.318
- REALLY?
- YEAH.

22:40.318 --> 22:43.237
LET'S GET THOSE BITCHES TUGGIN'.
- [chuckles]

22:44.697 --> 22:46.783
- [grunts]
- THERE YOU GO.

22:46.783 --> 22:50.912
- IT MEANS A LOT,
YOU LOOKING AFTER ME LIKE THIS.

22:50.912 --> 22:53.164
- OH.

22:53.164 --> 22:55.416
- I AM A LUCKY PUBLIC--
OH, JESUS CHR--OW!

22:55.416 --> 22:56.959
- HEY, BE CAREFUL!

22:56.959 --> 22:58.461
- NO, NO, IT'S FINE.
IT'S FINE.

22:58.461 --> 23:01.339
HE DIDN'T MEAN TO.
- NO.

23:01.339 --> 23:04.091
- DID YOU, CHUCKLES?
[laughs]

23:04.091 --> 23:06.052
FUNNY KID.

23:06.052 --> 23:10.973
- IT'S NICE TO BE WITH FAMILY.
- IT SURE IS. [sighs]

23:10.973 --> 23:13.976
[soft guitar music]

23:13.976 --> 23:21.984
♪ ♪

23:58.771 --> 24:00.231
- MORNING.

24:00.231 --> 24:02.567
- MORNING.
OH, PROBABLY NOT A GOOD TIME

24:02.567 --> 24:05.152
TO TELL FIONA ABOUT IAN.
- AND WHY IS THAT?

24:05.152 --> 24:07.489
- HER AND MIKE BROKE UP.
HEARD HER TALKING TO V.

24:07.489 --> 24:12.034
AND AFTER A BREAKUP, A WOMAN'S
NOT IN THE MOOD FOR BAD NEWS.

24:12.034 --> 24:15.664
- [chuckles]

24:15.664 --> 24:16.706
- HI, MIKE.

24:16.706 --> 24:19.041
SORRY FOR THE 15
STALKER VOICEMAILS.

24:19.041 --> 24:20.710
I'M ASSUMING YOU DON'T WANT
TO SEE MY FACE

24:20.710 --> 24:24.255
IN THE OFFICE, BUT MAYBE
I SHOULD COME GET MY STUFF.

24:24.255 --> 24:25.756
I'M NOT REALLY SURE
HOW TO HANDLE IT,

24:25.756 --> 24:30.678
SO, UH, CALL ME IF, UH...
YEAH.

24:32.680 --> 24:34.098
HEY.

24:34.098 --> 24:35.516
- DOESN'T SOUND LIKE
A FUN NIGHT.

24:35.516 --> 24:38.227
- EVERY TIME I CLOSE MY EYES,
I SEE MIKE.

24:38.227 --> 24:40.647
THE WAY HE LOOKED AT ME.
- MM.

24:40.647 --> 24:43.941
LAST NIGHT, AFTER A 16-HOUR
WORK DAY AT THE ALIBI,

24:43.941 --> 24:46.736
KEV AND I HEATED TATER TOTS
FOR DINNER.

24:46.736 --> 24:49.113
AND WHEN I PICKED UP
THOSE LITTLE BROWN LUMPS

24:49.113 --> 24:52.909
OUT OF THE MICROWAVE,
KEV MADE THIS FACE.

24:52.909 --> 24:55.537
THAT'S HOW YOU LOOK WHEN
YOU TALK ABOUT MIKE.

24:55.537 --> 24:56.954
- WHAT?
- MIKE'S A NICE GUY,

24:56.954 --> 24:58.372
BUT YOU WERE NEVER
THAT INTO HIM.

24:58.372 --> 24:59.832
- I HAVE NEVER MADE THAT FACE.

24:59.832 --> 25:02.418
- MIKE IS A TATER TOT.
- [sighs]

25:02.418 --> 25:04.003
THERE'S NO WAY
THAT HE DOESN'T FIRE ME.

25:04.003 --> 25:05.714
NOT TO MENTION,
HIS DAD OWNS THE COMPANY,

25:05.714 --> 25:07.590
AND HE WAS THERE LAST NIGHT.
- OUCH.

25:07.590 --> 25:09.759
- I WAS GETTING SO USED TO
A STEADY PAYCHECK.

25:09.759 --> 25:11.510
GROCERIES WITHOUT COUPONS,

25:11.510 --> 25:14.680
AND WINE IN A BOTTLE
INSTEAD OF A BOX.

25:14.680 --> 25:17.099
YOU THINK THEY'LL PAY ME
FOR LAST WEEK, OR JUST STIFF ME?

25:17.099 --> 25:20.519
[sighs]
OH, HEALTH INSURANCE.

25:20.519 --> 25:22.688
I MEAN, WE HAVE TO GET TO THE
DENTIST BEFORE THEY CANCEL IT.

25:22.688 --> 25:24.607
[footsteps approaching]

25:24.607 --> 25:26.317
- TOLD YOU.
- [sighs]

25:26.317 --> 25:28.444
MORNING.

25:28.444 --> 25:30.613
- HOLY SHIT!
WHEN DID YOU GET HOME?

25:30.613 --> 25:32.198
- LAST NIGHT.

25:32.198 --> 25:34.742
- SO GOOD TO SEE YOU.
- YEAH, YOU TOO.

25:34.742 --> 25:35.785
- UNLESS YOU FAILED OUT
OF SCHOOL.

25:35.785 --> 25:36.869
WHY ARE YOU HERE?

25:36.869 --> 25:39.080
- IT'S YOUR BIRTHDAY.

25:39.080 --> 25:40.539
- MY BIRTHDAY.

25:40.539 --> 25:41.999
- SHE WASN'T PLANNING
ON CELEBRATING WITH US,

25:41.999 --> 25:44.210
BUT NOW WE CAN HAVE
OUR PARTY HERE.

25:44.210 --> 25:45.628
KEV WILL BRING CHEAP BOOZE.

25:45.628 --> 25:47.254
LIKE, REALLY CHEAP.

25:47.254 --> 25:49.215
- I CAN PICK UP A CAKE
FROM THE SUPERMARKET.

25:49.215 --> 25:52.093
I KNOW THIS IS HARD.
- THANKS, DEBS.

25:52.093 --> 25:54.053
- HOPE THOSE AREN'T FOR US.

25:54.053 --> 25:56.180
- BACK TO BAG LUNCHES,
I'M AFRAID.

25:56.180 --> 25:57.974
BOLOGNA AND CHEESE.

25:57.974 --> 25:59.642
- YOU CAN'T JUST START GIVING US
LUNCH MONEY AND THEN CUT US OFF.

25:59.642 --> 26:02.770
- [sighs] I KNOW.
I'M SORRY.

26:02.770 --> 26:05.940
- IF MIKE WANTS TO FIRE YOU,
MAKE HIM ACT LIKE YOUR BOSS

26:05.940 --> 26:08.025
AND WRITE THAT SHIT
ON A HUMAN RESOURCE FORM.

26:08.025 --> 26:11.028
"I TERMINATED THIS EMPLOYEE
BECAUSE I WAS SCREWING HER,

26:11.028 --> 26:12.822
AND THEN SHE STARTED SCREWING
MY BROTHER."

26:12.822 --> 26:15.659
- YOU WHAT?
- REALLY?

26:15.659 --> 26:17.952
- MY BAD.
BUT SERIOUSLY, THIS SHIT

26:17.952 --> 26:20.997
IS THE DEFINITION
OF SEXUAL HARASSMENT.

26:20.997 --> 26:24.166
- SO I'M JUST GONNA GO INTO THE
OFFICE LIKE NOTHING HAPPENED,

26:24.166 --> 26:26.836
WITH EVERYONE STARING AT ME
AND HATIN' ME?

26:26.836 --> 26:28.879
- DO YOU NEED THE PAYCHECK
OR NOT?

26:30.631 --> 26:32.091
- WHERE ARE THE MASSAGE TABLES?

26:32.091 --> 26:33.718
- HEY, YOU KNOW HOW MUCH
THOSE THINGS COST?

26:33.718 --> 26:35.637
LOOK AT THIS, SALVATION ARMY,
10 BUCKS EACH.

26:35.637 --> 26:37.930
ALL WE GOTTA DO IS HANG SOME
SHEETS, DIVIDE THE SPACE UP.

26:37.930 --> 26:38.889
- YEAH, BUT WHAT ABOUT
THE CLEANUP?

26:38.889 --> 26:40.725
- WHAT ABOUT IT?

26:40.725 --> 26:41.892
- ISN'T THERE GONNA BE JIZZ
ALL OVER THE FLOOR?

26:41.892 --> 26:43.310
- YOU'RE OVER-THINKING THIS,
MAN.

26:43.310 --> 26:44.353
LOOK, WE'VE GOT EVERYTHING
WE NEED.

26:44.353 --> 26:46.230
LUBE, CLOROX, ALL IN BULK.

26:46.230 --> 26:49.233
- HOW MUCH WE CHARGE?
- 50 BUCKS, GIRLS GET 17.

26:49.233 --> 26:51.861
- 17?
SAME AS SASHA?

26:51.861 --> 26:53.362
AT LEAST OVER THERE,
WE HAVE WALLS.

26:53.362 --> 26:54.697
WE HAVE TABLES.
- YEAH, AND WE LEARNED

26:54.697 --> 26:57.074
A VALUABLE LESSON--
ANYONE CAN JERK A COCK.

26:57.074 --> 26:58.701
I JERK MINE, HE JERKS HIS.

26:58.701 --> 27:00.704
LEARN A UNIQUE SKILL
OR SHUT THE FUCK UP.

27:00.704 --> 27:02.788
- [speaking Russian]

27:02.788 --> 27:06.375
- NO ONE KNOWS WHAT
THE FUCK YOU'RE SAYING.

27:15.802 --> 27:17.720
- HI, FIONA.

27:28.105 --> 27:30.483
- FIONA.

27:30.483 --> 27:31.901
- GOOD MORNING.

27:31.901 --> 27:34.236
- CAN YOU COME WITH ME?
I NEED TO SPEAK WITH YOU.

27:34.236 --> 27:37.073
- EVERYTHING OKAY?
- BETTER IF WE SPEAK PRIVATELY.

27:46.665 --> 27:50.503
all: ♪ HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO YOU ♪

27:50.503 --> 27:54.090
♪ HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO YOU ♪

27:54.090 --> 27:58.552
♪ HAPPY BIRTHDAY, DEAR FIONA ♪

27:58.552 --> 28:02.306
♪ HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO YOU ♪

28:02.306 --> 28:05.726
- MAKE A WISH!

28:05.726 --> 28:07.561
OH...ATTAGIRL!

28:07.561 --> 28:10.689
- YEAH!
[applause]

28:10.689 --> 28:12.942
- GET SOME PLATES AND NAPKINS.
COME ON, WE'RE HUNGRY.

28:12.942 --> 28:14.902
GOT SOME CAKE TO EAT!

28:14.902 --> 28:18.364
DO YOU LIKE CHOCOLATE?
- YES!

28:18.364 --> 28:20.866
- I WANT TO HELP, BUT IF IAN
WANTED ME TO SHARE WHERE HE WAS,

28:20.866 --> 28:23.577
YOU'D ALREADY KNOW.
- HE CALLED YOU?

28:23.577 --> 28:25.788
- I DIDN'T SAY THAT.

28:25.788 --> 28:27.623
WHAT DO YOU KNOW
ABOUT IAN'S SEX LIFE?

28:27.623 --> 28:29.708
- WELL, HE'S GAY.

28:29.708 --> 28:32.336
- THERE'S AN OLD BOYFRIEND
OF IAN'S.

28:32.336 --> 28:34.923
- FROM HOW LONG AGO?
- NO, I MEAN LIKE "OLD" OLD.

28:34.923 --> 28:36.925
LIKE, OVER 40.

28:36.925 --> 28:38.592
I DON'T KNOW HIS NAME,
BUT IF YOU FIND HIM,

28:38.592 --> 28:40.136
ASK HIM ABOUT IAN.

28:40.136 --> 28:41.930
- ANYTHING?

28:41.930 --> 28:43.806
- YEAH, SAID WE SHOULD ASK
IAN'S OLD BOYFRIEND?

28:43.806 --> 28:45.015
SOMEONE WITH GRAY HAIR?

28:45.015 --> 28:47.893
- JIMMY'S DAD.

28:47.893 --> 28:51.815
HE CRAWLED INTO MY BED ONCE,
POKED ME WITH A FULL CHUB.

28:51.815 --> 28:53.816
- WAIT, YOU MEAN NED?
- YEAH, NED.

28:53.816 --> 28:56.819
- WAIT, SO JIMMY'S DAD
WAS IAN'S BOYFRIEND?

28:56.819 --> 28:58.863
- I'M NOT SURE THEY EVER MADE IT
TO BOYFRIEND STATUS,

28:58.863 --> 29:01.783
BUT, YEAH, THAT'S WHO MANDY'S
TALKING ABOUT.

29:01.783 --> 29:04.994
CHICAGO.
YEAH, DR. NED LISHMAN.

29:04.994 --> 29:07.789
- COME ON IN!

29:07.789 --> 29:10.875
RUNNING TREE, THIS IS FRANK'S
DAUGHTER, SAMMI,

29:10.875 --> 29:13.837
AND HER SON, CHUCK.

29:13.837 --> 29:15.296
- SORRY I'M LATE, SHEILA.

29:15.296 --> 29:17.006
I COULDN'T FIND ANYONE
TO WATCH THE KIDS.

29:17.006 --> 29:19.926
- OH, THAT'S NO--WHAT KIDS?

29:21.635 --> 29:24.597
OH.

29:24.597 --> 29:27.391
OH.

29:27.391 --> 29:29.143
- BROUGHT THE WHOLE TRIBE,
DID YA?

29:29.143 --> 29:31.813
- Y-YOU DIDN'T TELL ME
THAT YOU HAD KIDS.

29:31.813 --> 29:33.480
YOU NEVER MENTIONED IT.
- MY SISTER'S.

29:33.480 --> 29:36.567
SHE RAN OFF A FEW MONTHS AGO
WITH HER JUNKIE BOYFRIEND.

29:36.567 --> 29:41.197
- WELL, HELLO, AND WELCOME
TO ALL OF YOU.

29:41.197 --> 29:45.159
WHAT ARE YOUR NAMES?
- THIS IS DALE, BEN, SARAH,

29:45.159 --> 29:47.912
DENISE, AND GARY.

29:47.912 --> 29:49.788
- HELLO, GARY.

29:49.788 --> 29:51.207
WHAT'S YOUR INDIAN NAME?

29:51.207 --> 29:53.250
- GARY.

29:53.250 --> 29:56.921
- OH.
WELL, I'M SHEILA.

29:56.921 --> 29:58.589
JUST SHEILA.

29:58.589 --> 30:00.883
- WE'RE GONNA NEED SOME HELP
BUILDING THIS LODGE.

30:00.883 --> 30:02.426
THESE KIDS ARE USELESS.

30:02.426 --> 30:04.845
- WHAT DO YOU NEED?
- WELL, WE NEED A DOZEN

30:04.845 --> 30:08.140
7-FOOT SAPLINGS, 2 DOZEN
FIST-SIZED BASALTIC ROCKS,

30:08.140 --> 30:10.977
KINDLING, A COUPLE OF SHOVELS,
A PAIL OF WATER,

30:10.977 --> 30:15.064
AND ALL THE TARPS, QUILTS,
AND BUFFALO SKINS WE CAN FIND.

30:15.064 --> 30:16.732
- JESUS.

30:16.732 --> 30:18.734
[knock at door]
- COME IN.

30:22.363 --> 30:26.242
[sighs] I ASSUME THIS
IS PROFESSIONAL IN NATURE?

30:26.242 --> 30:28.535
- IT'S NOT,
BUT IT WON'T TAKE LONG.

30:28.535 --> 30:29.703
CAN I SHUT THE DOOR?

30:29.703 --> 30:31.705
- I'D PREFER YOU LEFT IT OPEN.

30:44.510 --> 30:46.512
- [sighs]

30:49.640 --> 30:52.393
I OWE YOU AN EXPLANATION,

30:52.393 --> 30:57.065
BECAUSE WHAT I DID WAS CRAZY.

30:59.233 --> 31:01.945
AND I KEEP ASKING MYSELF
WHY I DID IT.

31:03.862 --> 31:06.991
THE ONLY ANSWER THAT
I CAN COME UP WITH IS THAT

31:06.991 --> 31:09.952
I THINK I WAS TRYING
TO PROVE SOMETHING.

31:09.952 --> 31:14.290
NOT TO YOU, BUT TO MYSELF.

31:16.083 --> 31:20.964
PROVE THAT I DIDN'T
DESERVE YOU...

31:20.964 --> 31:26.885
OR THIS JOB, YOUR PARENTS,
YOUR FRIENDS...

31:26.885 --> 31:32.224
ALL THESE NICE, NORMAL,
FUNCTIONAL PEOPLE.

31:32.224 --> 31:34.852
I REALLY DIDN'T THINK
I DESERVED ANY OF IT.

31:39.315 --> 31:41.442
AND IN THE END, I WAS RIGHT.

31:46.697 --> 31:48.449
- THAT IT?

31:48.449 --> 31:50.451
- YEAH.

31:52.995 --> 31:54.830
ARE YOU FIRING ME?

31:54.830 --> 31:58.584
- NO. I AM TRANSFERRING YOU
TO ACCOUNT MANAGEMENT.

31:58.584 --> 32:00.711
I'D PREFER YOU DIDN'T WORK
FOR ME DIRECTLY.

32:04.715 --> 32:08.010
- THANK YOU.

32:08.010 --> 32:12.015
- I'M THE ONE WHO'S SORRY,
BY THE WAY.

32:12.015 --> 32:14.224
- WHY?

32:14.224 --> 32:17.019
- THAT I'M NOT MORE INTERESTING.

32:18.771 --> 32:20.064
- YOU ARE.

32:20.064 --> 32:22.691
- I'M REALLY NOT.
[chuckles]

32:22.691 --> 32:25.361
I HOLD DOWN A JOB,

32:25.361 --> 32:29.865
I LOOK AFTER MY FAMILY,
CARE ABOUT TELLING THE TRUTH.

32:29.865 --> 32:32.868
I'M SORRY THOSE AREN'T
SELLING POINTS.

32:35.371 --> 32:38.248
UM, IF YOU, UH...

32:38.248 --> 32:40.959
IF IT'S ALL RIGHT,
I'D LIKE YOU TO LEAVE NOW.

32:52.262 --> 32:54.264
- YOU'RE NOT DELIVERING
MY SUSHI, ARE YOU?

32:54.264 --> 32:56.433
- UH, NO, AFRAID NOT.

32:56.433 --> 32:57.768
- DO I KNOW YOU?

32:57.768 --> 33:01.189
- YEAH, I'M LIP.
IAN'S BROTHER.

33:01.189 --> 33:02.898
- OH, YEAH.

33:02.898 --> 33:04.191
OH, YEAH!

33:04.191 --> 33:06.652
- YEAH.
- HOW CAN I HELP YOU?

33:06.652 --> 33:08.612
I'M AFRAID JIMMY HASN'T BEEN
IN TOUCH FOR A WHILE.

33:08.612 --> 33:10.906
- WE'RE LOOKING FOR IAN.

33:10.906 --> 33:13.201
- HELLO!

33:13.201 --> 33:16.037
WHY DON'T YOU BOTH
COME INSIDE?

33:16.037 --> 33:18.288
- SURE, YEAH.
GO.

33:18.288 --> 33:19.873
- KNOW WHAT PISSES ME OFF?

33:19.873 --> 33:22.584
THAT CHRIS WON'T JUST SAY--

33:22.584 --> 33:23.669
HELLO.

33:23.669 --> 33:25.546
- YOU REALLY GOT A TYPE, HUH?

33:25.546 --> 33:27.339
- WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

33:27.339 --> 33:31.009
- UM, THESE ARE IAN'S SIBLINGS.

33:31.009 --> 33:33.303
- OH.
- GREAT, SO YOU BOTH KNOW HIM.

33:33.303 --> 33:35.514
WHERE CAN WE FIND HIM?

33:35.514 --> 33:38.350
- UM...I'LL LET YOU KNOW
WHEN THE FOOD COMES.

33:38.350 --> 33:40.436
- OKAY.

33:44.065 --> 33:46.066
- I LET IAN CRASH HERE
FOR A WHILE.

33:46.066 --> 33:48.069
- WHEN?
- A FEW WEEKS AGO.

33:48.069 --> 33:51.113
THEN I CAME HOME AND
HE WAS HOSTING A GROUP OF--

33:51.113 --> 33:55.076
WELL, IN MY OPINION--
UNSAVORY CHARACTERS.

33:55.076 --> 33:58.328
THEY SMASHED MY GLASS TABLETOP
WITH A BOTTLE OF JAGERMEISTER.

33:58.328 --> 34:00.956
WHEN THINGS SETTLED DOWN,
I ASKED IAN TO LEAVE.

34:00.956 --> 34:03.000
- WHERE DID HE GO?

34:03.000 --> 34:04.085
- WELL, HE'S WITH YOUR MOTHER.

34:04.085 --> 34:05.627
- MONICA?

34:05.627 --> 34:07.963
- GREAT, SO THEY'RE UNDER
A BRIDGE SOMEWHERE.

34:07.963 --> 34:09.673
- OH, IT WAS A HOUSE.

34:09.673 --> 34:11.508
I STILL HAVE THE ADDRESS.
YOU WANT IT?

34:11.508 --> 34:13.510
- YEAH, PLEASE.
- AH.

34:16.972 --> 34:19.933
- HEY, DEBS, WHY DON'T YOU, UH,
WHY DON'T YOU GO HOME, YEAH?

34:19.933 --> 34:21.477
- WHY?

34:21.477 --> 34:24.272
- JUST 'CAUSE EVERY TIME
WE FIND MONICA, YOU KNOW,

34:24.272 --> 34:26.356
WE WISH WE HADN'T.
SHE MIGHT NOT KNOW WHERE SHE IS,

34:26.356 --> 34:28.317
WHO SHE IS, WHO WE ARE.

34:28.317 --> 34:30.319
- I'M NOT A LITTLE KID.

34:32.696 --> 34:34.615
- OKAY.

34:34.615 --> 34:37.993
- THERE'S NO WAY I'M SHELLING
OUT 50 BUCKS FOR A HANDJOB.

34:37.993 --> 34:39.411
30, MAYBE.
- OKAY, I'LL TELL YOU WHAT.

34:39.411 --> 34:41.538
FOR 30 BUCKS,
YOU CAN GO JERK YOURSELF OFF.

34:41.538 --> 34:43.749
- WE'VE GOT OVERHEAD, TOMMY.
THE LAUNDRY ALONE IS KILLING--

34:43.749 --> 34:45.334
- HEY, I PAY 30
AT THE THAI PLACE,

34:45.334 --> 34:47.085
AND THEY WASH TOWELS TOO.

34:47.085 --> 34:49.713
- DAMN THAI SEX WORKERS,

34:49.713 --> 34:52.049
STEALING JOBS
FROM DECENT AMERICANS.

34:52.049 --> 34:53.050
- OUR GIRLS ARE RUSSIAN.

34:53.050 --> 34:54.051
- THEY EAT WITH FORKS,

34:54.051 --> 34:55.677
NOT WITH STICKS, RIGHT?

34:55.677 --> 34:57.138
- BABY, YOU HIT UP EVERYONE
WHO'S COME IN HERE,

34:57.138 --> 34:58.722
ALL THREE OF 'EM.

34:58.722 --> 35:01.308
- WHAT IF WE ADVERTISE?
PUT AN AD IN CRAIGSLIST

35:01.308 --> 35:02.768
OR ONE OF THOSE FREE
LOCAL BUSINESS THINGS?

35:02.768 --> 35:03.894
- HEY, YEAH, WE CAN GET
SOME METH HEADS

35:03.894 --> 35:05.103
TO HAND OUT FLYERS AND SHIT.

35:05.103 --> 35:06.688
- AND PAY THEM HOW?
- WE DON'T.

35:06.688 --> 35:07.981
WE JUST TELL THEM
WE'LL PAY 'EM,

35:07.981 --> 35:09.149
AND IF THEY COMPLAIN ABOUT IT,

35:09.149 --> 35:10.776
WE'LL BEAT THE SHIT
OUT OF THEM.

35:15.239 --> 35:17.032
- CARL!

35:17.032 --> 35:18.575
CARL!

35:18.575 --> 35:19.826
CARL, HEY.

35:19.826 --> 35:22.205
[grunts]
I GOT A JOB FOR YOU, SON.

35:22.205 --> 35:23.247
- I'M BUSY.

35:23.247 --> 35:26.166
- NO, THIS IS--THIS IS BETTER.

35:26.166 --> 35:28.377
WE'RE GONNA BUILD A SWEAT LODGE.

35:28.377 --> 35:32.422
GREAT BIG ROCKS, HEATED BY
A BIG FIRE, AND A TEEPEE--

35:32.422 --> 35:35.217
- BIG FIRE?
- YEAH.

35:35.217 --> 35:38.387
OH, THIS IS SAMMI,
YOUR BIG SISTER.

35:38.387 --> 35:40.973
IT'S TIME YOU MET.
- HI!

35:40.973 --> 35:42.599
- HI.

35:42.599 --> 35:44.059
I ALREADY GOT TWO SISTERS.

35:44.059 --> 35:45.477
- YEAH, WELL,
HERE'S ANOTHER ONE.

35:45.477 --> 35:47.020
- THIS IS YOUR NEPHEW.

35:47.020 --> 35:50.482
CHUCKY, BABY,
THIS IS YOUR UNCLE, CARL.

35:50.482 --> 35:53.902
WOW, THEY EVEN LOOK ALIKE.

35:53.902 --> 35:56.197
OH, SHIT.

35:56.197 --> 35:58.156
THIS IS AN EMOTIONAL SITUATION.

35:58.156 --> 36:00.450
- CAN I TALK TO YOU
FOR A SECOND?

36:00.450 --> 36:03.203
- EXCUSE US, WOULD YOU?
- SURE.

36:03.203 --> 36:05.373
- SHE'S FREAKING ME OUT.
- I GET IT.

36:05.373 --> 36:08.333
LOOK, HOW ABOUT I TAKE SAMMI TO
THE ALIBI FOR REINFORCEMENTS?

36:08.333 --> 36:10.127
YOU AND CHUCK GATHER SAPLINGS.

36:10.127 --> 36:12.838
YOU CAN INITIATE HIM INTO
THE GALLAGHER WAY.

36:12.838 --> 36:15.090
[laughs]

36:15.090 --> 36:19.219
- WAIT, WHAT'S A SAPLING?
- [laughs]

36:19.219 --> 36:23.890
- SO WHAT HAPPENED
WITH THIS, UH, BOYFRIEND?

36:23.890 --> 36:26.893
- EX-BOYFRIEND.
HIS NAME'S MATT.

36:26.893 --> 36:29.438
HE'S NICE, BUT HE SAID
WE COULDN'T BE TOGETHER

36:29.438 --> 36:32.274
BECAUSE I'M A VIRGIN, SO
I TRIED IT WITH SOMEONE ELSE--

36:32.274 --> 36:34.276
- WAIT, TRIED?

36:34.276 --> 36:35.277
- SEX.

36:35.277 --> 36:36.862
- WITH WHO?

36:36.862 --> 36:40.824
- SETH ESPARELLI,
IN THE ARCADE BATHROOM.

36:40.824 --> 36:42.451
- JESUS, DEBS.

36:42.451 --> 36:46.038
- ONLY, IT DIDN'T WORK,
AND I THINK WE BROKE UP?

36:46.038 --> 36:47.873
I MEAN, I GUESS.

36:47.873 --> 36:50.751
I HAVEN'T REALLY CALLED HIM
TO, LIKE--

36:50.751 --> 36:54.630
- CONFIRM?
- NO--YEAH.

36:54.630 --> 36:57.966
[sighs]
SO STRESSFUL.

36:57.966 --> 36:59.968
- YEAH.

37:08.435 --> 37:10.437
- WHAT THE HELL?

37:17.611 --> 37:20.281
- I WARNED YOU NOT TO TEST ME.

37:20.281 --> 37:23.450
- WHO ARE THESE GUYS?
- MY INTRAMURAL TENNIS TEAM.

37:23.450 --> 37:27.704
AND TRUST ME,
THEY DO NOT MESS AROUND.

37:27.704 --> 37:29.373
DO YOU HAVE MY CASH?

37:29.373 --> 37:30.957
- WAIT, ARE YOU ALL GAY?
- NO.

37:30.957 --> 37:32.292
- I'M NOT TRYING TO
BE INSULTING,

37:32.292 --> 37:35.462
I JUST WANT TO KNOW IF YOU...
WANT A HANDJOB.

37:41.718 --> 37:43.720
- WELL, NED SAID
THIS IS THE PLACE.

37:43.720 --> 37:45.972
- DOESN'T LOOK LIKE ANYONE
LIVES HERE.

37:48.475 --> 37:50.560
WAIT, LIP, DON'T GO IN THERE.

37:50.560 --> 37:53.355
- I KIND OF HAVE TO, RIGHT?

37:53.355 --> 37:56.233
HEY, COME ON,
JUST STAY BEHIND ME.

37:56.233 --> 37:57.526
HERE WE GO.

38:04.449 --> 38:07.953
- LET'S GO HOME.
- IT'S OKAY, DEBS.

38:07.953 --> 38:10.706
SOMEONE'S GOT THE HEAT ON.

38:15.043 --> 38:17.254
THIS IS IAN'S.

38:17.254 --> 38:21.466
YO, IAN!
- [indistinct singing]

38:21.466 --> 38:22.718
- SOMEONE'S COMING.

38:22.718 --> 38:26.096
- [indistinct singing]

38:26.096 --> 38:27.390
- SHIT.

38:27.390 --> 38:29.349
- AAH!

38:29.349 --> 38:30.350
- SORRY!
- I HAVE GOT A GUN,

38:30.350 --> 38:32.018
YOU MOTHERFUCKERS!

38:32.018 --> 38:33.145
I WILL SHOOT YOU FULL OF HOLES!

38:33.145 --> 38:34.896
- NO, PLEASE DON'T DO THAT!

38:34.896 --> 38:37.482
WE'RE JUST LOOKING
FOR OUR BROTHER!

38:37.482 --> 38:38.525
- LOOKING FOR WHO?

38:38.525 --> 38:40.694
- IAN GALLAGHER?

38:40.694 --> 38:43.989
OR--OR MONICA?
SHE LIVE HERE?

38:43.989 --> 38:45.323
- WHO ARE YOU?

38:45.323 --> 38:47.410
- DO YOU REALLY HAVE A GUN?
- YEAH!

38:47.410 --> 38:49.327
AND MONICA DON'T LIVE HERE
NO MORE.

38:49.327 --> 38:51.580
- OKAY, LOOK, THIS IS
OUR BROTHER'S STUFF, OKAY?

38:51.580 --> 38:53.540
SO HE LIVES HERE, RIGHT?

38:53.540 --> 38:55.333
LOOK, WE'RE JUST TRYING
TO FIND HIM.

38:55.333 --> 38:56.501
- HE'S AT WORK.

38:56.501 --> 38:57.711
- AND WHERE'S THAT?

38:57.711 --> 38:59.421
- [sighs]
THE WHITE SWALLOW.

38:59.421 --> 39:00.756
- WAIT, THE WHAT?

39:00.756 --> 39:03.967
- THE WHITE SWALLOW,
IN BOYSTOWN.

39:03.967 --> 39:05.343
- ALL RIGHT, THANK YOU.
THANK YOU.

39:05.343 --> 39:06.762
GO, DEBS, GO.
GO, GO, GO, GO, GO.

39:06.762 --> 39:08.431
[Locksley's She Does]

39:08.431 --> 39:12.184
- ♪ YOW! ♪

39:12.184 --> 39:14.352
- COME ON, HURRY UP!

39:14.352 --> 39:18.190
♪ ♪

39:18.190 --> 39:22.611
- ♪ COME ON, HONEY,
YOU KNOW WHAT YOU DO, YEAH ♪

39:22.611 --> 39:25.113
♪ NOBODY DOES IT LIKE SHE DOES ♪

39:25.113 --> 39:27.575
♪ NOBODY DOES IT
LIKE SHE DOES ♪

39:27.575 --> 39:29.535
♪ NOBODY DOES IT LIKE SHE DOES ♪

39:30.702 --> 39:35.373
[indistinct chatter, laughter]

39:35.373 --> 39:36.666
- HERE YOU GO,
HERE'S YOUR CHANGE,

39:36.666 --> 39:38.794
AND VERONICA WILL TAKE CARE
OF YOU.

39:38.794 --> 39:41.087
- NICE.
- EXCUSE ME?

39:41.087 --> 39:42.088
- NO, NOT HER.
FORGET IT.

39:42.088 --> 39:43.424
MICKEY!
- YEAH?

39:43.424 --> 39:44.633
- GOT A CUSTOMER
TO TAKE UPSTAIRS.

39:44.633 --> 39:47.052
- RIGHT THIS WAY, MCENROE.
[phone rings]

39:47.052 --> 39:48.386
- ALIBI.

39:48.386 --> 39:50.222
- IT'S ME.
- HEY! I WAS JUST ABOUT TO

39:50.222 --> 39:51.640
CALL YOU.
WE'RE GONNA BE A COUPLE

39:51.640 --> 39:53.058
OF MINUTES LATE
'CAUSE WE HAVE CUSTOMERS

39:53.058 --> 39:54.810
AT THE BAR FOR
THE FIRST TIME IN DAYS.

39:54.810 --> 39:56.228
- YEAH, I WAS CALLING
TO SAY I'M NOT

39:56.228 --> 39:57.896
REALLY MUCH IN THE MOOD
FOR A PARTY.

39:57.896 --> 39:59.773
- WELL, THAT'S TOO DAMN BAD,
'CAUSE KEV AND I

39:59.773 --> 40:02.317
ARE COMING OVER WITH A GALLON
OF "IVAN THE TERRIBLE" VODKA

40:02.317 --> 40:04.236
AND A BUCKET
OF COOL RANCH DORITOS.

40:04.236 --> 40:05.529
IF YOU DON'T WANT TO PARTAKE,
YOU CAN WATCH.

40:05.529 --> 40:07.739
[knock at door]
- DOOR'S OPEN!

40:07.739 --> 40:08.907
I DON'T HAVE A CHOICE?

40:08.907 --> 40:10.116
- BYE, BITCH.

40:10.116 --> 40:12.118
- [sighs]
[door closes]

40:15.747 --> 40:16.915
ARE YOU KIDDIN' ME?

40:16.915 --> 40:18.416
- HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

40:18.416 --> 40:20.126
- WHAT THE FUCK
ARE YOU DOING HERE?

40:20.126 --> 40:21.670
- WELL, I THOUGHT
WE COULD CELEBRATE TOGETHER.

40:21.670 --> 40:24.506
- OR I COULD STAB MYSELF
IN THE EYE WITH A PENCIL.

40:24.506 --> 40:25.924
- BY WAY OF APOLOGIZING.

40:25.924 --> 40:28.885
NOW IT'S A PARTY.
- COKE?

40:28.885 --> 40:31.597
FRESH OUT OF REHAB,
AND YOU HAVE COKE?

40:31.597 --> 40:32.514
- WELL, BOOZE IS THE PROBLEM.

40:32.514 --> 40:34.307
I CAN DO COKE, A LITTLE WEED.

40:34.307 --> 40:35.892
BUT AS FAR AS BOOZE GOES,
I'M CLEAN.

40:35.892 --> 40:37.060
- YOU SOUND LIKE FRANK.

40:37.060 --> 40:38.604
- WHO'S FRANK?

40:38.604 --> 40:39.604
OH, YOU GOT A MIRROR?

40:39.604 --> 40:41.022
- OH, YEAH, RIGHT HERE.

40:41.022 --> 40:43.191
OH, WAIT, IT'S A BASEBALL BAT.

40:43.191 --> 40:45.694
- HEY!
WHOA, EASY, EASY.

40:45.694 --> 40:47.821
WHOA, WHOA.
OKAY, OKAY.

40:47.821 --> 40:49.698
ALL RIGHT. [chuckles]
HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

41:00.792 --> 41:03.712
[club music]

41:03.712 --> 41:11.344
♪ ♪

41:27.819 --> 41:29.404
- DOES HE KNOW IT'S US?

41:29.404 --> 41:32.532
- YEAH, I THINK SO.
YO!

41:32.532 --> 41:35.911
- WHAT'S UP?

41:35.911 --> 41:37.245
HEY, MAN.
OH.

41:37.245 --> 41:38.830
- [laughs]
DEBBIE!

41:38.830 --> 41:39.956
OH, MY GOSH.

41:39.956 --> 41:42.959
YOU LOOK GREAT!
- THANK YOU.

41:42.959 --> 41:44.545
YOU DO TOO.

41:44.545 --> 41:45.754
- THIS IS MY BROTHER AND SISTER.

41:45.754 --> 41:47.047
THIS IS FAMILY!

41:47.047 --> 41:48.674
- HEY.
- [laughs]

41:48.674 --> 41:51.092
- HEY, HOW LONG
YOU BEEN WORKING HERE, HUH?

41:51.092 --> 41:52.720
- A COUPLE WEEKS.
- YEAH?

41:52.720 --> 41:53.887
- THIS PLACE, IT'S AWESOME.

41:53.887 --> 41:55.639
IT'S--IT'S SUPER CONVENIENT.

41:55.639 --> 41:57.891
YOU GUYS WANT DRINKS?
THEY'RE ON THE HOUSE.

41:57.891 --> 41:59.267
- NO, I'M GOOD, I'M GOOD.
- APPLETINI, APPLETIN--

41:59.267 --> 42:00.603
- NO.
- TWO APPLETINIS.

42:00.603 --> 42:03.313
- OKAY.

42:03.313 --> 42:05.566
- HEY, IAN, IS THERE ANYPLACE
WE COULD TALK?

42:05.566 --> 42:08.526
- OH, I LOVE THIS SONG!

42:08.526 --> 42:11.613
- YEAH, LOOK, SOME ARMY M.P.s
CAME BY LOOKING FOR YOU.

42:11.613 --> 42:14.532
THEY WANT TO ARREST YOU
FOR GOING AWOL,

42:14.532 --> 42:18.161
STEALING GOVERNMENT PROPERTY.
- THIS IS TOP-SHELF.

42:18.161 --> 42:19.580
- NO, HEY,
DID--DID YOU HEAR ME?

42:19.580 --> 42:21.289
THEY SAY YOU STOLE
A HELICOPTER.

42:21.289 --> 42:23.416
- [laughs]
THAT'S HILARIOUS.

42:23.416 --> 42:25.251
- IS IT?

42:25.251 --> 42:27.379
- YEAH, YEAH, I MEAN,
I DIDN'T STEAL ANYTHING,

42:27.379 --> 42:29.005
I JUST STARTED THE ROTORS.

42:29.005 --> 42:31.216
HEY, CAN YOU GUYS HANG AROUND
FOR A WHILE?

42:31.216 --> 42:33.009
MY SHIFT GETS OFF AT 2:00,

42:33.009 --> 42:35.220
BUT I ALWAYS GO OUT AFTER,
OR HIT THE LOCAL GYM,

42:35.220 --> 42:36.680
DEPENDING ON HOW PUMPED I AM.

42:36.680 --> 42:40.809
BUT SEEING YOU GUYS, I-I JUST--
I FEEL GREAT, YOU KNOW?

42:40.809 --> 42:42.560
- OKAY, YOU KNOW WHAT,
HEY, LET'S GO OUTSIDE

42:42.560 --> 42:44.020
SO WE CAN HEAR EACH OTHER, HUH?

42:44.020 --> 42:45.313
- TRY YOUR DRINK.
- NO, OUTSIDE.

42:45.313 --> 42:47.315
COME ON, COME HERE.
- [laughs]

42:47.315 --> 42:49.484
- HEY, GET YOUR HAND OFF HIM.
- NO, IT'S FINE, IT'S OKAY.

42:49.484 --> 42:51.653
WE'RE BROTHERS, ALL RIGHT?
WE'RE JUST TALKING. YO, IAN!

42:51.653 --> 42:52.904
- AND I DEFINITELY NEED
SOME I.D.

42:52.904 --> 42:54.280
- COME ON, IAN!
- LET'S GO!

42:54.280 --> 42:55.615
- SHE'S NOT DRINKING, MAN.
IAN!

42:55.615 --> 42:57.867
YO!

42:59.119 --> 43:00.662
- WHY WAS HE ACTING LIKE THAT?

43:00.662 --> 43:02.080
- IT'S LATE.
WE SHOULD GO.

43:02.080 --> 43:03.790
- IS THERE SOMETHING WRONG
WITH HIM?

43:03.790 --> 43:05.668
- AT LEAST WE KNOW WHERE
HE IS NOW, OKAY?

43:05.668 --> 43:07.670
I'LL COME BACK AND CHECK ON HIM.

43:07.670 --> 43:09.713
LET'S GET YOU HOME, THOUGH,
ALL RIGHT?

43:09.713 --> 43:10.588
COME ON.

43:10.588 --> 43:12.215
[Native American music]

43:12.215 --> 43:16.219
- THIS IS GONNA MAKE YOU FEEL
RIGHT AT HOME.

43:16.219 --> 43:18.304
OKAY.

43:18.304 --> 43:22.726
I'VE GOT SUCCOTASH, QUINOA,
AND FRYBREAD

43:22.726 --> 43:27.522
MADE FROM ACORN POWDER,
INDIGENOUS TO OUR PEOPLE.

43:27.522 --> 43:29.107
WHAT WAS YOUR NAME AGAIN?

43:29.107 --> 43:30.650
- ONE-EYED SNAKE.

43:30.650 --> 43:33.654
AND THIS IS STINKING WIND.

43:33.654 --> 43:36.448
- STINKING WIND.

43:36.448 --> 43:37.949
THAT'S UNUSUAL.

43:37.949 --> 43:39.784
- GOT ANY BURGERS?

43:39.784 --> 43:41.704
- BUFFALO BURGERS.
I'VE GOT BUFFALO BURGERS.

43:41.704 --> 43:43.455
WOULD YOU LIKE THAT?
LET ME GET THAT FOR YOU.

43:43.455 --> 43:44.956
HOLD ON A SECOND.

43:44.956 --> 43:48.668
HOLD ON, HOLD ON,
MISSY, HOLD ON.

43:48.668 --> 43:50.712
- DUMB SHIT, WHY ARE YOU GIVING
HER FAKE NAMES?

43:50.712 --> 43:53.465
- 'CAUSE SHE'S CRAZY.
- AT LEAST SHE MADE US DINNER.

43:53.465 --> 43:57.052
♪ ♪

43:57.052 --> 43:59.512
- TIE IT TIGHT.
NICE AND TIGHT.

43:59.512 --> 44:01.347
YEAH, GOOD, GOOD.
- YEAH, WE MADE IT!

44:01.347 --> 44:03.141
- HOLY SHIT.
- OKAY!

44:03.141 --> 44:07.812
[all chattering]

44:07.812 --> 44:08.855
- WHOO, MAN!

44:08.855 --> 44:10.565
- DAD, DAD, DAD, DAD, DAD.

44:10.565 --> 44:11.691
LOOK WHAT WE BUILT.

44:11.691 --> 44:13.151
WE TOOK IT FROM
A WHOLE PILE OF TREES

44:13.151 --> 44:14.486
FROM THE PVC,
AND THEN WE GOT--

44:14.486 --> 44:16.237
- SAMMI WAS AMAZING!

44:16.237 --> 44:18.490
SHE RALLIED THE BAR
BY TELLING THEM THE LODGE

44:18.490 --> 44:21.785
WOULD CURE IMPOTENCE,
AND THEN SHE LED THE CHARGE

44:21.785 --> 44:24.287
TO STEAL BLANKETS FROM THE BUMS
ON SKID ROW.

44:24.287 --> 44:26.832
IS SHE A CHIP OFF
THE OLD BLOCK OR WHAT?

44:26.832 --> 44:28.666
- ALL FOR A GOOD CAUSE.

44:28.666 --> 44:30.126
- JESUS, THEY REEK.

44:30.126 --> 44:32.713
- YEAH, WELL,
THEY'LL KEEP THE HEAT IN.

44:32.713 --> 44:34.757
COME ON, GUYS, LET'S GO.

44:40.887 --> 44:42.680
[indistinct chatter]

44:42.680 --> 44:46.976
- YAY!
[cheers and applause]

44:46.976 --> 44:48.937
- ALL RIGHT, ALAN, HERE'S $350.

44:48.937 --> 44:50.688
I'LL GIVE YOU THE REST
IN A COUPLE OF DAYS.

44:50.688 --> 44:53.024
- YOU KNOW, KEVIN,
THE IDEA OF MEN UPSTAIRS,

44:53.024 --> 44:55.151
JIZZING ALL OVER
DAD'S APARTMENT...

44:55.151 --> 44:56.945
[laughs]
WORKS FOR ME.

44:56.945 --> 45:00.115
- TELL YOUR FRIENDS, OKAY?

45:00.115 --> 45:02.826
- ALL RIGHT, BABE,
LET TITO HERE TAKE OVER.

45:02.826 --> 45:04.787
WE GOT TO GET TO FIONA'S.
- ALL RIGHT, JUST ONE MORE SHOT.

45:04.787 --> 45:07.790
HERE'S TO GOOD OLD FASHIONED
AMERICAN CAPITALISM.

45:07.790 --> 45:09.207
YOU CAN KEEP A MAN DOWN.

45:09.207 --> 45:11.793
BUT YOU CAN NEVER KEEP HIM
FROM GETTING IT UP.

45:11.793 --> 45:13.628
- YES, SIR!
- MM.

45:13.628 --> 45:15.713
- OW! LET'S GO, LET'S GO!
- YEAH.

45:15.713 --> 45:18.007
- CHIEF SAYS COVER ALL
THE HOLES, COME ON.

45:20.468 --> 45:24.806
- DAD, WHEN SAMMI WAS LITTLE,
DID YOU EVER THINK ABOUT HER?

45:24.806 --> 45:27.350
- OF COURSE I DID.
[exhales]

45:27.350 --> 45:30.395
WELL, NO, I DIDN'T, BUT THAT HAD
MORE TO DO WITH HER MOTHER.

45:30.395 --> 45:32.021
SHE WAS A REAL PAIN IN THE ASS.

45:32.021 --> 45:33.815
- HOW COME?

45:33.815 --> 45:38.736
- SHE WANTED ME TO...GET A JOB,
SUPPORT THEM, YADA, YADA, YADA.

45:38.736 --> 45:40.280
HOW OLD ARE YOU NOW, TEN?

45:40.280 --> 45:41.990
- 12.
- WELL, SOON YOU'LL KNOCK UP

45:41.990 --> 45:44.075
YOUR FIRST GHETTO GIRL
AND DITCH HER.

45:44.075 --> 45:49.205
BUT, YOU GET TO MY AGE,
YOU GET PERSPECTIVE.

45:49.205 --> 45:51.875
YOU LEARN TO EMBRACE
THE RESPONSIBILITIES

45:51.875 --> 45:54.794
THAT COME WITH PARENTHOOD.

45:54.794 --> 45:57.798
SAMMI'S MY LAST CHANCE
TO GET IT RIGHT.

45:57.798 --> 46:00.175
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
"GET IT RIGHT"?

46:00.175 --> 46:01.844
- HUH?

46:01.844 --> 46:03.386
- I GOTTA GO.

46:03.386 --> 46:05.305
- NOW?
YOU'RE GONNA MISS THE CEREMONY.

46:05.305 --> 46:07.098
- SEE YA.

46:10.393 --> 46:11.769
- SOON AS I CARRY
THESE HOT ROCKS

46:11.769 --> 46:14.063
INTO THE LODGE, WE'RE READY.

46:14.063 --> 46:15.815
YOU OKAY?

46:15.815 --> 46:17.650
- MY SON JUST TOOK OFF.

46:17.650 --> 46:19.444
- HUH, LOOK AT MY SISTER'S KIDS.

46:19.444 --> 46:21.362
WE'RE OUT HERE BUILDING A
TRADITIONAL FUCKING SWEAT LODGE,

46:21.362 --> 46:24.073
THEY'RE IN THERE WATCHING TV.
FUCK 'EM.

46:24.073 --> 46:25.575
- [laughs]
- [snorts]

46:25.575 --> 46:28.996
[shouts]

46:28.996 --> 46:30.914
- MOVE THAT ARM!
- OH!

46:30.914 --> 46:32.165
- MOVE THAT ARM!
- [laughs]

46:32.165 --> 46:33.583
- MOVE THAT ARM, MOVE THAT ARM!

46:33.583 --> 46:36.502
LIAM'S BREAKING IT DOWN!
- [laughs]

46:36.502 --> 46:38.838
- OH!
- [laughs]

46:38.838 --> 46:40.673
HI!

46:40.673 --> 46:44.510
- ♪ YOU'LL GET HIGH
ONCE YOU WANT TO ♪

46:44.510 --> 46:46.804
- I DON'T CARE IF I CAN'T DRINK
OR TAKE YOUR DRUGS!

46:46.804 --> 46:48.806
I GOT DORITOS!
DORITOS ARE LIKE CRACK!

46:48.806 --> 46:50.683
I MIGHT EVEN SNORT 'EM.

46:50.683 --> 46:54.062
- ♪ YOU CAN'T HAVE ANY WARNING ♪
- [laughs]

46:54.062 --> 46:55.981
- OH!

46:55.981 --> 46:58.901
WELL, AT LEAST ROBBIE GOT
ONE THING RIGHT, THE PRICK.

46:58.901 --> 47:00.526
- FIONA, GET YOUR ASS IN HERE!

47:00.526 --> 47:02.070
I'M GONNA SHOW YOU
HOW TO BREAK IT DOWN!

47:02.070 --> 47:03.488
UNH, UNH.

47:03.488 --> 47:05.198
- COMING.
- OH!

47:05.198 --> 47:06.950
- ♪ YOU'VE GOT GUM STUCK
IN YOUR HAIR ♪

47:06.950 --> 47:13.289
[laughter, shouting]

47:13.289 --> 47:14.832
- OH, WHOO!

47:14.832 --> 47:18.045
[chattering, whooping]

47:19.671 --> 47:21.214
- OKAY, GO ON.

47:21.214 --> 47:26.052
[muffled music]

47:26.052 --> 47:29.097
HEY, DEBS.

47:29.097 --> 47:31.724
THANKS FOR COMING WITH ME TODAY.

47:31.724 --> 47:33.476
- YEAH, THANKS FOR LETTING ME.

47:33.476 --> 47:35.728
- ♪ YOU CAN HAVE ANYTHING
YOU WANT ♪

47:35.728 --> 47:37.689
♪ YOU CAN HAVE IT ALL ♪

47:37.689 --> 47:40.316
♪ IF YOU JUST PULL
YOURSELF TOGETHER ♪

47:40.316 --> 47:41.693
both: HEY!

47:41.693 --> 47:43.861
- HEY!
- LOOK AT LIP NOW!

47:43.861 --> 47:46.239
- CAKE, CAKE, CAKE, CAKE!
- OH, OH!

47:49.867 --> 47:51.327
- WHERE YOU BEEN?

47:51.327 --> 47:52.787
- OH, WE JUST ON
A LITTLE ADVENTURE.

47:52.787 --> 47:54.706
I'LL TELL YOU
ALL ABOUT IT LATER.

47:54.706 --> 47:56.541
- WELL, LOOKS LIKE SOMEBODY'S
GONNA GET TO KEEP THEIR JOB!

47:56.541 --> 47:58.084
- OH, NO SHIT, THAT'S GREAT.
- MM-HMM.

47:58.084 --> 48:00.920
- FIONA!

48:00.920 --> 48:02.380
OH, MY GOD.
- WHAT?

48:02.380 --> 48:03.840
- OH, SHIT.
- WHAT'S ON HIS FACE?

48:03.840 --> 48:05.508
- OH, MY GOD, OH, MY GOD,
OH, MY GOD.

48:05.508 --> 48:07.010
- STEP BACK, STEP BACK.
- OH, MY GOD.

48:07.010 --> 48:08.136
- STEP BACK.
- HE'S NOT BREATHING!

48:08.136 --> 48:09.679
- OH, MY GOD.
- OH, MY GOD.

48:09.679 --> 48:11.764
OH, MY GOD, OH, MY GOD.
- LIAM? LIAM? LIAM?

48:11.764 --> 48:14.017
- OH, MY GOD, CALL!
- LIAM?

48:14.017 --> 48:16.019
LIAM?
STEP BACK, GIVE HIM SOME ROOM.

48:16.019 --> 48:17.020
LIAM?

48:17.020 --> 48:18.939
- OH, MY GOD.
- LIAM?

48:20.983 --> 48:23.986
- COPY THAT.
COMING INBOUND WITH ONE CHILD.

48:23.986 --> 48:26.696
B.P. IS 200 OVER 120.
HEART RATE'S 130.

48:26.696 --> 48:28.156
- OH, MY GOD, OH, MY GOD.

48:28.156 --> 48:29.907
- WHAT'D HE TAKE?

48:29.907 --> 48:31.534
- COKE!
HE GOT INTO MY COKE.

48:31.534 --> 48:32.952
- HOW MUCH?
- A HALF GRAM, MAYBE MORE.

48:32.952 --> 48:34.412
I DON'T KNOW.

48:34.412 --> 48:36.080
- COMING THROUGH.
- HE GONNA BE OKAY?

48:36.080 --> 48:37.165
HE'S GONNA BE OKAY,
THOUGH, RIGHT?

48:37.165 --> 48:39.083
- YEAH, CLEAR THE WAY, PLEASE.

48:39.083 --> 48:40.710
COMING THROUGH!

48:40.710 --> 48:42.170
- THREE-YEAR-OLD MALE,
COCAINE INGESTION.

48:42.170 --> 48:44.172
B.P.'S 200 OVER 120.
H.R. IS 130.

48:44.172 --> 48:45.715
- HE'S GONNA BE OKAY, RIGHT?
- STARTED 2 MILLIGRAMS

48:45.715 --> 48:46.841
OF ATIVAN, 12 MINUTES OUT.

48:46.841 --> 48:48.010
- HE'S GONNA BE OKAY, RIGHT?

48:48.010 --> 48:52.764
[radio chatter]

49:05.693 --> 49:09.197
- ♪ ARE YOU STILL ♪

49:09.197 --> 49:11.407
[doors close]
[siren wails]

49:11.407 --> 49:14.952
- I'LL GET THE TRUCK.

49:14.952 --> 49:22.044
♪ ♪

49:22.044 --> 49:23.836
[siren wailing]
- THANK YOU, GREAT SPIRIT,

49:23.836 --> 49:27.049
FOR THIS BLESSING, FOR THE GOOD
EARTH, PLANTS, AND TREES.

49:27.049 --> 49:29.176
THE UNIVERSAL LIFEBLOOD
OF OUR SWEAT

49:29.176 --> 49:31.344
INTERMINGLES WITH THE WATERS
OF THE WORLD,

49:31.344 --> 49:34.014
CARRIED TO THE FOUR QUARTERS
OF THE PLANET.

49:34.014 --> 49:36.265
WE KNOW YOU, HEALING SPIRIT,
WHEN YOU ARE WITH US.

49:36.265 --> 49:39.186
YOUR VOICE IS THE VOICE
OF ALL THINGS.

49:39.186 --> 49:42.022
YOU CALL TO US--
- [bullhorn] FRANK GALLAGHER!

49:42.022 --> 49:44.357
- AAH!
- JESUS CHRIST!

49:50.780 --> 49:52.824
- WOW, IT'S HOT.

49:52.824 --> 49:54.283
HEY, IS FRANK IN HERE?

49:54.283 --> 49:56.369
IT'S ABOUT HIS SON, LIAM.

49:59.206 --> 50:00.248
- DAD?

50:00.248 --> 50:03.084
- BEAT 5533,
I NEED AN AMBULANCE.

50:15.555 --> 50:17.348
- THEY WON'T LET ME BACK THERE.

50:17.348 --> 50:19.016
I WAS WATCHING HIM AT THE PARTY.

50:19.016 --> 50:22.187
I THOUGHT HE WAS IN
THE LIVING ROOM.

50:22.187 --> 50:24.147
EXCUSE ME, LIAM?
LIAM GALLAGHER?

50:24.147 --> 50:25.731
- HAVE A SEAT.

50:25.731 --> 50:29.235
SOMEONE WILL BE OUT
WITH YOU IN A MINUTE.

50:29.235 --> 50:30.695
- WHAT WAS THAT?

50:30.695 --> 50:32.113
- WHO'S FIONA?

50:32.113 --> 50:33.573
- THAT'S ME.

50:33.573 --> 50:34.782
- PUT YOUR HANDS
BEHIND YOUR BACK.

50:34.782 --> 50:36.492
- WHAT?

50:36.492 --> 50:38.661
- FIONA GALLAGHER, YOU HAVE
THE RIGHT TO REMAIN SILENT.

50:38.661 --> 50:39.954
- WHOA, WHOA,
WHOA, WHAT'S GOING ON?

50:39.954 --> 50:41.205
- ANYTHING YOU SAY
CAN AND WILL BE

50:41.205 --> 50:42.540
USED AGAINST YOU
IN A COURT OF LAW.

50:42.540 --> 50:43.541
YOU HAVE THE RIGHT
TO AN ATTORNEY.

50:43.541 --> 50:45.042
IF YOU CANNOT AFFORD ONE,

50:45.042 --> 50:47.044
ONE WILL BE APPOINTED TO YOU.
[handcuffs click]

50:47.044 --> 50:48.546
DO YOU UNDERSTAND YOUR RIGHTS
AS I'VE READ THEM TO YOU?

50:48.546 --> 50:51.549
[soft rock music]

